\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ113093\add* EhudВҰ113107 approached where the king was sittingВҰ113099 aloneВҰ113105 inВҰ113100 the coolnessВҰ113101 of his upper room andВҰ113093 told him, вҖңI have a messageВҰ113108 for youВҰ113112 from GodВҰ113110.вҖқ \add @The king\add* stood up from \add &his\add* seatВҰ113115
\v 21 and thenВҰ113117 EhudВҰ113118 reachedВҰ113117 withВҰ113131 his left handВҰ113121 and pulled the sword from his rightВҰ113129 thighВҰ113128 and plunged it into \add @the king's\add* bellyВҰ113131.
\v 22 Even the handle went in afterВҰ113137 the blade andВҰ113133 the fat closedВҰ113139 up over the handle because \add @Ehud\add* didn'tВҰ113144 pull the sword out of his bellyВҰ113147. ThenВҰ113133 he went out to the passage\f + \fr 3:22 \ft The meaning of the last word in the Hebrew here is uncertain, so other translations might differ.\f*
\v 23 and closedВҰ113154 and lockedВҰ113158 the rooms of the upper room and exited through the porchВҰ113153.\f + \fr 3:23 \ft Again, the Hebrew meaning of the last word here is uncertain, so other translations might differ.\f*
\v 24 AfterВҰ113173 he'd left, the servantsВҰ113162 cameВҰ113163 andВҰ113160 found the doorsВҰ113166 lockedВҰ113168, so they thought \add @the king\add* must be relieving himselfВҰ113175 inВҰ113176 \add *there\add*.
\v 25 TheyВҰ113194 waitedВҰ113179 untilВҰ113180 they \add вүҲbecame worried\add* that he hadn't opened the doorsВҰ113189, \add вүҲso\add* they got a key andВҰ113179 opened \add them\add*, only to find theirВҰ113199 masterВҰ113199 lyingВҰ113200 deadВҰ113202 on the floor.
\p
\v 26 While \add @the servants\add* had been waiting, Ehud had escaped andВҰ113204 passedВҰ113209 beyond the quarries, thenВҰ113204 fleeing to Seirah.
\v 27 WhenВҰ113216 he got there, he blew a trumpetВҰ113219 \add вүҲthroughout\add* the EfrayimiteВҰ113221 hill country, andВҰ113216 \add so\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ113226 assembled under his direction\add* down \add inВҰ113217 the valley\add*.
\v 28 вҖңFollow after me,вҖқ he told them, вҖңbecause YahwehВҰ113240 \add вүҲwill enable you all to defeat your enemiesВҰ113243, the Moabites\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ113233 they followed him down to the YordanВҰ113254 \add river\add* andВҰ113233 capturedВҰ113250 the fordsВҰ113253 opposite MoabВҰ113246, thus preventing anyoneВҰ113259 from crossingВҰ113260.
\v 29 ThenВҰ113262 theyВҰ113262 \add вүҲattacked MoabВҰ113265 and killed around tenВҰ113268 thousandВҰ113269 men\add*вҖ”all strong and capable yet none of them escapedВҰ113279.
\v 30 \add вүҲSoВҰ113282\add* MoabВҰ113283 was subduedВҰ113282 that dayВҰ113284 by the IsraelisВҰ113288, andВҰ113282 \add вүҲthere was peaceВҰ113289 in the region\add* for eightyВҰ113291 years.
