\v 1 TheВҰ114266 IsraelisВҰ114261 did \add вүҲthings that YahwehВҰ114264 considered evilВҰ114262 so\add* \add *he\add* handed them over to the MidianВҰ114269 for sevenВҰ114270 yearsВҰ114271
\v 2 and the \add вүҲMidianites oppressed\add* \add *them\add* badly. \add вүҲIt was so bad thatВҰ114290 the IsraelisВҰ114286\add* made dens for themselves up in the hills, in cavesВҰ114294, and \add вүҲin small, fortified settlements\add*.
\v 3 Whenever the Israelis planted a crop, the Midianites or the AmalekitesВҰ114306, or easternВҰ114309 groups wouldВҰ114304 attack \add #them\add*.
\v 4 They would set up their camps around them and destroyВҰ114315 the crops as far away as GazaВҰ114323вҖ”theyВҰ114326 left \add вүҲnothing for the Israelis to eat\add*, and \add вүЎno\add* \add #sheep, cattle, or donkeysВҰ114331\add*.
\v 5 It was like a swarmВҰ114340 of locustsВҰ114342 when they'd \add all\add* come with their tentsВҰ114337 and their livestockВҰ114335вҖ”you couldn't even count their camelsВҰ114345! They entered the region to \add вүҲtotally ravage\add* itВҰ114350.
\v 6 Thus YisraelВҰ114353 was \add вүҲseverely weakened\add* by MidianВҰ114356, andВҰ114357 the IsraelisВҰ114360 criedВҰ114357 out to YahwehВҰ114363.
\p
\v 7 When the IsraelisВҰ114372 criedВҰ114369 out to YahwehВҰ114375 concerning MidianВҰ114378,
\v 8 Yahweh sent a prophetВҰ114383 to \add *them\add* andВҰ114380 he told them, вҖңYisrael'sВҰ114387 godВҰ114395 Yahweh says, вҖҳI myself brought you all out of slaveryВҰ114404 in EgyptВҰ114400вҖ”
\v 9 rescuing you from the Egyptians who were oppressingВҰ114413 you all. I droveВҰ114414 them out \add вүҲwhen you all entered\add* andВҰ114406 I've certainly given theirВҰ114421 land to you.
\v 10 I told you all that I'm your godВҰ114427 YahwehВҰ114426 andВҰ114423 that when you live inВҰ114437 the AmoriteВҰ114433 regionsВҰ114437, you all mustn't worship theirВҰ114437 godsВҰ114432. ButВҰ114423 you \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ114428 listenВҰ114439 to what I saidВҰ114423\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Call of Gideon
\p
\v 11 \add One day\add* Yahweh's messengerВҰ114444 cameВҰ114443 and satВҰ114446 beneath the oak tree in \add the town of\add* OfrahВҰ114450. (The tree belongedВҰ114452 to the Abi-EzriteВҰ114454, YoashВҰ114452.) Yoah's son GideonВҰ114455 was beatingВҰ114457 wheatВҰ114458 \add down\add* in a winepressВҰ114459 to hideВҰ114460 it from the Midianites
\v 12 when Yahweh's messengerВҰ114466 appearedВҰ114464 to him andВҰ114464 saidВҰ114471, вҖңYahweh is with you, you powerful warrior.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖңWith me, my masterВҰ114482?вҖқ GideonВҰ114480 \add вүҲasked\add*. вҖңIf Yahweh is withВҰ114509 us, thenВҰ114478 why's all of this happenedВҰ114487 to us? Where are all of the miracles thatВҰ114495 ourВҰ114499 ancestorsВҰ114499 told us about, saying, вҖҳDidn't Yahweh bringВҰ114503 us up out of EgyptВҰ114502?вҖҷ ButВҰ114478 now Yahweh has abandonedВҰ114506 us andВҰ114478 handed us over to the Midianites.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ114513 YahwehВҰ114515 turnedВҰ114513 to him andВҰ114513 saidВҰ114516, вҖңUse yourВҰ114518 strengthВҰ114518 to set YisraelВҰ114523 free from the grasp of MidianВҰ114525. Haven't I sentВҰ114527 you \add to do that\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңPlease, my masterВҰ114532,вҖқ Gideon replied, вҖңhow could \em I\em* save YisraelВҰ114537? Look, my clan is the weakestВҰ114540 in MenashshehВҰ114541 andВҰ114542 \add onВҰ114533 top of that\add*, I'm the youngestВҰ114543 in my \add вүҲfamilyВҰ114539\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңI'llВҰ114551 \add вүҲhelp\add* you,вҖқ saidВҰ114547 YahwehВҰ114549, вҖңandВҰ114553 you'll strikeВҰ114553 down all the MidianitesВҰ114556 as \add easily as battling just\add* one manВҰ114557.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңIf indeed I'veВҰ114565 foundВҰ114565 favourВҰ114566 inВҰ114567 yourВҰ114567 eyesВҰ114567,вҖқ Gideon \add вүҲrequested\add*, вҖңthenВҰ114560 \add вүҲshow me a miracle so I'll know that it's God\add* speakingВҰ114572 to me.
\v 18 Please \add вүҲwait here\add* \add while I go and prepare\add* my giftВҰ114587 for you and bringВҰ114584 it back here for you.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Okay,\add* I'llВҰ114592 stay \add here\add* until you get back,вҖқ heВҰ114590 saidВҰ114590.
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ114596 GideonВҰ114596 wentВҰ114597 a prepared a young goat and unrisen breadВҰ114605. He put the meat in a basketВҰ114608 and the soup in a pot and broughtВҰ114612 them out to the oak tree and offered them to him.
\v 20 Then God's messengerВҰ114623 saidВҰ114621, вҖңTake the meat and the flat breadВҰ114631 and put them on this rockВҰ114635, then pour the soup out \add over it\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* \add @Gideon\add* did that
\v 21 and Yahweh's messenger stretchedВҰ114644 out the staffВҰ114650 thatВҰ114651 he was holding and touchedВҰ114653 the meat and bread withВҰ114654 the endВҰ114649 of it. A fireВҰ114657 flamed up from the rockВҰ114660 and burnt up the meat and bread, thenВҰ114644 Yahweh's messenger went out of his sightВҰ114671.\f + \fr 6:21 \ft It's unclear from the text, whether he just got up and walked away, or if he vanished in a more miraculous fashion.\f*
\p
\v 22 WhenВҰ114673 GideonВҰ114674 \add вүҲrealisedВҰ114673\add* that it \add really\add* had been Yahweh's messenger, he \add вүҲwas upset andВҰ114673 said\add*, вҖңOh no, my masterВҰ114684 Yahweh, \add вүҲwhat will happen now that\add* I'veВҰ114691 seen Yahweh's face to face?вҖқ
\v 23 ButВҰ114699 YahwehВҰ114701 \add вүҲreplied\add* to him, вҖңPeace to you. Don't be afraidВҰ114706вҖ”you won'tВҰ114704 dieВҰ114708.вҖқ
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ114710\add* GideonВҰ114712 builtВҰ114710 an altarВҰ114713 there to \add sacrifice\add* to Yahweh andВҰ114710 named it вҖҳYahweh is peaceВҰ114719вҖҷ. (It's stillВҰ114723 stands there atВҰ114724 OfrahВҰ114724 of the Abi-Ezrite to this dayВҰ114721.)
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲThat same\add* nightВҰ114730, YahwehВҰ114734 told him, вҖңTake the youngВҰ114738 bull that belongs to your father, and the secondВҰ114744 bull sevenВҰ114745 yearsВҰ114746 old. Break the altarВҰ114750 of BaalВҰ114751 into pieces that belongs to your father, and cut down the AsherahВҰ114756 pole that's beside it.
\v 26 Build a \add вүҲregular\add* altarВҰ114763 to yourВҰ114765 godВҰ114765 YahwehВҰ114764 onВҰ114770 top of this strongholdВҰ114768, thenВҰ114762 takeВҰ114771 the secondВҰ114775 bullВҰ114774 andВҰ114762 offer a whole burntВҰ114777 offeringВҰ114777 using the AsherahВҰ114779 pole thatВҰ114780 youВҰ114781 cut down \add вүҲfor firewood\add*.вҖқ
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ114783\add* GideonВҰ114784 took ten of his servantsВҰ114787 and did what YahwehВҰ114792 had instructed him to, \add вүҲbutВҰ114783\add* he did it at nightВҰ114807 because he was afraidВҰ114795 to do it in the daytimeвҖ”\add fearing the anger of\add* his father'sВҰ114799 householdВҰ114798 and the men of the cityВҰ114803.
\rem /s1 Gideon Destroys the Altar of Baal
\p
\v 28 WhenВҰ114809 the menВҰ114810 of the cityВҰ114811 got up earlyВҰ114809 the next morningВҰ114812, wow, the Baal'sВҰ114816 altar had been torn down, the AsherahВҰ114817 pole that was beside it had been cut down, andВҰ114809 the secondВҰ114824 bullВҰ114823 had been offeredВҰ114825 onВҰ114812 a \add new\add* altar that had been builtВҰ114829.
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ114831\add* people started asking each other, вҖңWho did this?вҖқ After some investigationВҰ114840, they said, вҖңYoash'sВҰ114846 son GideonВҰ114843 did it.вҖқ
\v 30 ThenВҰ114851 the menВҰ114852 of the cityВҰ114853 told YoashВҰ114856, вҖңBring your son out \add here\add* \add вүҲto be executed\add*, becauseВҰ114868 he tore down the Baal'sВҰ114867 altarВҰ114866 andВҰ114851 cut down the AsherahВҰ114870 \add pole\add* thatВҰ114871 was beside it.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖң\add вүҲAre you all really fighting Baal'sВҰ114885 battle for him\add*?вҖқ YoashВҰ114876 replied to thoseВҰ114878 standing against him. вҖңAre you all really helping him? Whoever fights on his behalf shouldВҰ114902 be be put to deathВҰ114894 while it is still the morningВҰ114897. If \add @Baal\add* is a godВҰ114900, thenВҰ114875 let him stand up for himself when someoneВҰ114905 tears down his altarВҰ114908.вҖқ
\v 32 \add вүҲSoВҰ114910 after that\add*, he calledВҰ114910 \add @Gideon\add* вҖҳYerub-BaalвҖҷ to sayВҰ114917 вҖҳLet Baal defend himself,вҖҷ because he had torn down \add @Baal's\add* altarВҰ114925.
\p
\v 33 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* all the Midianite and Amalekite \add warriors\add* and others from the east, assembled togetherВҰ114936. Then theyВҰ114935 crossedВҰ114937 the Yordan and set up camp inВҰ114939 the Jezreel valleyВҰ114939.
\v 34 \add вүҲButВҰ114942\add* Yahweh'sВҰ114943 spiritВҰ114942 \add вүҲenabled\add* GideonВҰ114947, and heВҰ114948 blew a trumpetВҰ114949 and calledВҰ114950 the \add men of\add* AbiezerВҰ114954 to followВҰ114955 himВҰ114955.
\v 35 ThenВҰ114957 he sent messengers throughout all of \add the regions of\add* MenashshehВҰ114961, AsherВҰ114972, ZebulunВҰ114973, and NaftaliВҰ114974, and summoned \add their warriors\add* to come and join withВҰ114972 them.
\rem /s1 The Sign of the Fleece
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ114978 GideonВҰ114979 said to GodВҰ114982, вҖңIfВҰ114988 it's \add really\add* you rescuing YisraelВҰ114990 \add вүҲthrough me\add* like you said,
\v 37 I'll put this woollen fleece on the threshingВҰ115001 floorВҰ115001 \add tonight\add*. If there's dew on the fleece inВҰ115001 the morning, butВҰ115009 it's dry around it, then I'll knowВҰ115015 that you'll rescue YisraelВҰ115022 \add вүҲthrough me\add* just as you said.вҖқ
\v 38 AndВҰ115032 that's what happenedвҖ”he rose earlyВҰ115029 the next morningВҰ115030 and squeezedВҰ115031 the fleece and wrungВҰ115035 out a bowl full of waterВҰ115042 from the dew.
\v 39 ThenВҰ115044 GideonВҰ115045 saidВҰ115044 to GodВҰ115048, вҖңDon't \add вүҲbe angry with me\add*, but \add вүҲcan I ask one more thing\add*. Let me put the fleece out this timeВҰ115062, andВҰ115044 let the fleece be dry, but wet all around it with dew.вҖқ
\v 40 \add вүҲSoВҰ115081\add* GodВҰ115082 did it that nightВҰ115084, andВҰ115081 \add the next morning\add* only the fleeceВҰ115091 was dry, butВҰ115081 everywhere around was covered withВҰ115084 dew.
\c 7
\s1 Gideon defeats the Midianites
\rem /s1 Gideon Defeats the Midianites; Gideon Surprises and Routs the Midianites
\p
\v 1 Then GideonВҰ115105 (\add also known as\add* Yerub-Baal) and the warriors withВҰ115124 him got up earlyВҰ115102 and \add went to\add* HarodВҰ115115 spring. The Midianite campВҰ115116 was northВҰ115121 of them inВҰ115124 the valleyВҰ115124 belowВҰ115122 the MorehВҰ115123 hill.
\p
\v 2 ThenВҰ115126 YahwehВҰ115127 told GideonВҰ115130, вҖң\add вүҲYou've got too many warriors withВҰ115139 youВҰ115134 for me to giveВҰ115135 victory over the Midianites, because what if YisraelВҰ115144 takes the glory for themselves thinking thatВҰ115133 theirВҰ115139 own strength saved them\add*.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ115150\add* tell the men that anyone who's afraid or tremblingВҰ115159 can leaveВҰ115161 Mt. GileadВҰ115163 andВҰ115150 goВҰ115160 back home.вҖқ Twenty-two thousand of them went back, leaving \add only\add* tenВҰ115171 thousand.\x + \xo 7:3: \xt Deu 20:8.\x*
\p
\v 4 вҖңThat's stillВҰ115181 too many,вҖқ YahwehВҰ115177 told GideonВҰ115180. вҖңBring them down to the \add вүҲspring\add* and I'llВҰ115194 short-list them thereВҰ115191. Whoever I tell you to go with you, can do so, butВҰ115176 anyone that I say won't go with you, won't go.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ115217\add* he took them down to the water andВҰ115217 YahwehВҰ115226 told \add *him\add*, вҖң\add вүҲSeparateВҰ115229 out those\add* who lap up the water with \add #their tonguesВҰ115234\add* like a dog would, \add вүҲalong with those\add* who kneel down to drinkВҰ115251.вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲIt turned out\add* that \add only\add* threeВҰ115260 hundredВҰ115261 men used their handsВҰ115256 to bring water to their mouthsВҰ115259, andВҰ115253 all the rest knelt down to drinkВҰ115270 the water.
\v 7 вҖңI'llВҰ115283 \add вүҲrescue\add* youВҰ115284 all from MidianВҰ115288 withВҰ115279 the threeВҰ115279 hundredВҰ115280 men who lappedВҰ115282 the water \add from their hands\add*,вҖқ YahwehВҰ115275 told GideonВҰ115278. вҖңLetВҰ115285 all the others goВҰ115293 back to their homes.вҖқ
\v 8 ThenВҰ115297 the three-hundred warriors \add вүҲcollected\add* the food andВҰ115297 ram's horns from the others before \add @Gideon\add* sentВҰ115310 the others back to their own \add вүҲhomes\add*.
\p TheВҰ115309 MidianВҰ115319 campВҰ115318 was below \add #them\add* \add down\add* inВҰ115302 the valleyВҰ115323
\v 9 and during the nightВҰ115327 YahwehВҰ115331 told \add @Gideon\add*, вҖң\add вүҲGet ready\add* and \add lead them\add* down into the campВҰ115334, because I have \add вүҲmade you victorious\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ115339\add* if you're afraidВҰ115341 to \add вүҲattack\add*, take yourВҰ115347 servantВҰ115347 PurahВҰ115346 down to \add &their\add* campВҰ115350
\v 11 and you'll hearВҰ115352 what they're saying, thenВҰ115352 \add вүҲyou'll have the courage to goВҰ115359 down\add* \add and attack\add* the camp.вҖқ SoВҰ115352 \add @Gideon\add* and his servantВҰ115364 PurahВҰ115363 went \add quietly\add* down to the \add вүҲunit\add* atВҰ115360 the edge of the camp.
\p
\v 12 The Midianites and AmalekitesВҰ115373 and others from the east covered the valleyВҰ115380 like a swarm of locustsВҰ115381. \add Even\add* theirВҰ115383 camelsВҰ115383 were as numerous as sand grains onВҰ115380 the beach.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ115393\add* GideonВҰ115394 \add вүҲgot close\add*, a man was telling his companion about his dream. вҖңListen,вҖқ he said, вҖңI had a dream and wow, a roundВҰ115406 loaf of barleyВҰ115409 breadВҰ115408 was tumblingВҰ115410 into \add вүҲour\add* campВҰ115411. It came as far as the tent and struckВҰ115417 it so that it fell and turnedВҰ115419 it upside down, and collapsedВҰ115421 \add completely\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲThat could only be\add* the swordВҰ115432 of Yoash'sВҰ115436 son GideonВҰ115433 from YisraelВҰ115438,вҖқ \add вүҲthe other manВҰ115437\add* replied. вҖңThe true GodВҰ115440 has \add вүҲcaused MidianВҰ115444 andВҰ115424 all of the camp to be defeated by him\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 When GideonВҰ115454 heardВҰ115453 the account of the dreamВҰ115458 and its interpretationВҰ115461, he \add вүҲthanked God\add*, then \add #they\add* returnedВҰ115463 to \add *their\add* camp and \add вүҲcommanded\add*, вҖң\add вүҲGet ready to go\add* because YahwehВҰ115473 has givenВҰ115472 \add вүҲyou all victory over\add* the Midianite camp.вҖқ
\v 16 ThenВҰ115481 he dividedВҰ115480 the three hundredВҰ115485 men into three units, and gaveВҰ115489 each of them rams' horns and \add clay\add* jars withВҰ115491 \add burning\add* torchesВҰ115496 inside them,
\v 17 and instructed them, вҖңWatch me and do what I do. See, when I get to the edge of \add &their\add* campВҰ115510, do the same as me.
\v 18 WhenВҰ115518 I blow the ram's horn trumpetВҰ115519, all of youВҰ115529 withВҰ115519 horns should blow them and \add everyone\add* will shout, вҖҳFor YahwehВҰ115535 and for GideonВҰ115536!вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲWhen\add* Gideon and the hundredВҰ115541 men withВҰ115547 him got to the edge of the campВҰ115548, it was the beginningВҰ115549 of the middleВҰ115551 nightwatch and \add вүҲthe fresh guards had just gotten into their places\add*. \add @Gideon and his unit\add* blew their trumpetsВҰ115559 and smashedВҰ115560 the jars \add вүҲthatВҰ115562 theyВҰ115554 were carrying\add*.
\v 20 ThenВҰ115565 \add all\add* threeВҰ115566 units blew the trumpets and smashed their jars. They held the torchesВҰ115576 in their left hands and the trumpets in their rightВҰ115579 hands, and they shouted out, вҖңA swordВҰ115583 for YahwehВҰ115584 and for GideonВҰ115585.вҖқ
\v 21 ThenВҰ115587 everyoneВҰ115588 stoodВҰ115587 in their placeВҰ115589 around the campВҰ115591, \add вүҲbutВҰ115587\add* the \add Midianite\add* army criedВҰ115596 out \add in alarm\add* andВҰ115587 \add вүҲtook off\add*.
\v 22 WhenВҰ115600 the threeВҰ115601 hundredВҰ115603 ram's horns \add вүҲsounded\add*, YahwehВҰ115606 \add вүҲcaused the Midianite army to start fighting each other withВҰ115610 their swordsВҰ115608\add*, and the army fled as far as Beyt-ShittahВҰ115619 (towards TsererahВҰ115620) and towards the borderВҰ115622 of Avel-Meholah (towards TabbatВҰ115628).
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ115630 the \add вүҲwarriors\add* from NaftaliВҰ115634, AsherВҰ115637, andВҰ115630 from all of MenashshehВҰ115642 were summonedВҰ115630 \add вүҲto help with pursuingВҰ115643 the Midianites\add*.
\v 24 GideonВҰ115649 \add also\add* sentВҰ115648 messengersВҰ115647 through Efrayim'sВҰ115653 hill countryВҰ115652 \add вүҲto tell them\add*, вҖңGo down \add to the Yordan river\add* opposite MidianВҰ115657 and \add вүҲtake control of the crossings to captureВҰ115658 them between\add* as far as Beyt-Barah.вҖқ SoВҰ115647 all the men of Efrayim were summonedВҰ115669 and theyВҰ115674 commandeered the Yordan \add вүҲcrossings\add* as far as Beyt-Barah.
\v 25 They chased after the Midianites and capturedВҰ115685 their two princes, Oreb and Zeeb. They killed Oreb at the rock \add now called\add* вҖҳOreb'sВҰ115692 rockвҖҷ, and they killed Zeeb at a winepress \add now called\add* вҖҳZeeb'sВҰ115695 winepressвҖҷ, and they broughtВҰ115718 their headsВҰ115714 back across the YordanВҰ115723 to GideonВҰ115721.
\c 8
\s1 The final defeat of the Midianites
\rem /s1 Gideon Kills Zebah and Zalmunna; Gideon's Triumph and Vengeance; The Final Defeat of the Midianites
\p
\v 1 \add ButВҰ115725\add* thenВҰ115725 the Efrayimite men \add вүҲchallenged\add* Gideon, вҖңWhy have you \add вүҲside-tracked\add* us? Why didn'tВҰ115735 you call us when you wentВҰ115739 to battle againstВҰ115741 the Midianites?вҖқ And they severely rebuked him.
\p
\v 2 вҖңWhat \add вүҲhave I achieved comparedВҰ115752 to youВҰ115752 guys\add*?вҖқ \add вүҲanswered\add* \add @Gideon\add*. вҖңAren't the \add вүҲseconds\add* of Efrayim'sВҰ115756 grapes better than the \add whole\add* grapeВҰ115757 harvestВҰ115757 of AbiezerВҰ115758?
\v 3 GodВҰ115762 \add вүҲhelped you all defeat\add* OrebВҰ115769 and ZeebВҰ115772, the princes of MidianВҰ115766. What did I do comparedВҰ115777 to that?вҖқ After he saidВҰ115782 that, they \add all\add* \add вүҲcalmed down againВҰ115781\add*.\x + \xo 8:3-5: \xt Psa 83:11.\x*
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ115786 GideonВҰ115787 andВҰ115786 his threeВҰ115791 hundredВҰ115793 warriors crossed the YordanВҰ115788 \add going east\add*. They were \add вүҲall exhaustedВҰ115797, butВҰ115786 continued the pursuitВҰ115798\add*.
\v 5 \add WhenВҰ115800 they arrived atВҰ115810 the town\add* of Sukkot, Gideon asked the \add вүҲleaders\add*, вҖңPlease giveВҰ115803 my menВҰ115801 some breadВҰ115807 to eat because they're exhaustedВҰ115813, \add вүҲbutВҰ115800 we're chasingВҰ115816\add* ZebahВҰ115818 andВҰ115800 ZalmunnaВҰ115819, the Midianite kingsВҰ115820.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲHowever, the Sukkot officialsВҰ115824 asked\add* \add cautiously\add*, вҖң\add вүҲDo you already have ZebahВҰ115827 andВҰ115823 ZalmunnaВҰ115828 inВҰ115830 your grasp\add* that weВҰ115833 should giveВҰ115833 \add вүҲfoodВҰ115835\add* to \em your\em* army?вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖңLet me assure you all,вҖқ GideonВҰ115838 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ115837\add*, вҖңthat when YahwehВҰ115841 has \add вүҲhelped us capture ZebahВҰ115844 and ZalmunnaВҰ115847\add*, I will rip off yourВҰ115852 fleshВҰ115852 withВҰ115840 the wildernessВҰ115856 thornsВҰ115855 and briersВҰ115859.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 From there they climbed up to PenuelВҰ115863, and he \add вүҲasked them for food in a similar manner\add*, and the \add вүҲleaders there\add* responded similarly to the \add вүҲleaders\add* of Sukkot.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ115876\add* he saidВҰ115876 to the menВҰ115879 of PenuelВҰ115880 as well, вҖңWhenВҰ115876 I returnВҰ115882 \add вүҲsafely\add*, I'llВҰ115884 tear down this towerВҰ115887.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲNow\add* ZebahВҰ115891 and ZalmunnaВҰ115892 were inВҰ115893 KarkorВҰ115893 withВҰ115893 around fifteen thousand warriorsвҖ”all that remainedВҰ115900 out of all of that allied Midianite camp of easternВҰ115905 peopleВҰ115903, because one hundredВҰ115907 and twentyВҰ115908 thousand of theirВҰ115894 warriors had already been killed.
\v 11 GideonВҰ115915 approached them \add unexpectedly\add* via the caravan route east of NobahВҰ115920 and JogbehahВҰ115921, and struck their camp when they were feeling secureВҰ115928.
\v 12 ZebahВҰ115931 and ZalmunnaВҰ115932 fled, butВҰ115930 \add #they\add* chased afterВҰ115934 those twoВҰ115938 Midianite kingsВҰ115940 and capturedВҰ115935 them, thus defeating their entireВҰ115948 army.
\p
\v 13 The GideonВҰ115954 (Yoash'sВҰ115957 son) \add andВҰ115953 his warriors\add* returnedВҰ115953 from battleВҰ115960, going through the HeresВҰ115962 pass.
\v 14 He capturedВҰ115964 a youngВҰ115966 man from Sukkot and questionedВҰ115969 himвҖ”writing down the names of the seventy-seven leaders and eldersВҰ115978 of Sukkot.
\v 15 ThenВҰ115983 he \add вүҲreturned to\add* Sukkot and told them, вҖңLook \add here\add* atВҰ116000 Zebah and ZalmunnaвҖ”the ones you tauntedВҰ115993 me about when you \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖҳ\add вүҲDo you already have Zebah and Zalmunna inВҰ116000 your grasp\add* that we should give \add вүҲfoodВҰ116005\add* to your wearyВҰ116004 men.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 16 HeВҰ116023 tookВҰ116007 the cityВҰ116011 eldersВҰ116010 and \add had them punished\add* with wildernessВҰ116015 thornsВҰ116014 and briersВҰ116018 \add вүҲto teach them a lesson\add*,
\v 17 thenВҰ116025 \add they went to\add* PenuelВҰ116028 and tore down the towerВҰ116027 and executed the cityВҰ116034 \add вүҲleaders\add*.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ116036 \add @Gideon\add* \add вүҲasked\add* ZebahВҰ116039 andВҰ116036 ZalmunnaВҰ116042, вҖң\add вүҲWhat were the menВҰ116044 like\add* that you killedВҰ116046 atВҰ116047 TaborВҰ116047?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲThey were just like you\add*,вҖқ they \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲThey seemed like they could have been a king's sonsВҰ116056\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңThey were my brothersВҰ116060вҖ”the sonsВҰ116061 of my motherВҰ116063,вҖқ he saidВҰ116059. вҖңAs YahwehВҰ116067 lives, if only you had let them liveВҰ116069, I wouldn't have killedВҰ116072 you.вҖқ
\v 20 ThenВҰ116075 he \add вүҲordered\add* Yeter, his oldest son, вҖңGo andВҰ116075 killВҰ116079 them.вҖқ ButВҰ116075 Yeter didn'tВҰ116081 pull out his swordВҰ116085 because he was afraidВҰ116087вҖ”he was stillВҰ116089 a youth.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ116092 Zebah and Zalmunna saidВҰ116092, вҖңCome and kill us yourselfвҖ”\add вүҲbe a manВҰ116101 and use your own strengthВҰ116102\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ116092 GideonВҰ116104 \add вүҲwent over\add* and killedВҰ116105 Zebah and Zalmunna, and thenВҰ116092 he tookВҰ116112 the crescent-shaped ornamentsВҰ116115 thatВҰ116116 were onВҰ116099 theirВҰ116118 camels' necksВҰ116117.
\rem /s1 Gideon's Idolatry; Gideon's Sacred Ephod; Gideon's Ephod
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ116120 \add a group of\add* IsraeliВҰ116123 men saidВҰ116120 to GideonВҰ116126, вҖң\add вүҲWe want you and your sons and your future descendants to\add* rule over us, because you have \add вүҲsaved us from the Midianites\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲButВҰ116145\add* GideonВҰ116147 \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖң\add No,\add* I won'tВҰ116148 rule over you myself, nor will my son rule over you. YahwehВҰ116158 will rule over you.вҖқ
\v 24 \add вүҲHowever\add*, \add *he\add* \add вүҲcontinuedВҰ116162\add*, вҖңLet me askВҰ116165 youВҰ116166 all for something: that each man giveВҰ116168 me the \add #earrings\add* from his spoil.вҖқ (\add @The enemies\add* had goldВҰ116177 earrings because theyВҰ116181 were IshmaelitesВҰ116180.)
\p
\v 25 вҖңWeВҰ116187 \add вүҲcan certainly do that for you\add*,вҖқ they \add вүҲreplied\add*. SoВҰ116183 they spreadВҰ116186 out a garmentВҰ116189 andВҰ116183 each man threwВҰ116190 the \add #earrings\add* from his spoil onto it.
\v 26 Now the weightВҰ116197 of the gold earringsВҰ116198 of gold came to twenty kilograms, andВҰ116196 thenВҰ116196 there were the crescent-shaped ornamentsВҰ116210, the pendantsВҰ116211, the dyed purpleВҰ116213 garmentsВҰ116212 that the Midianite kingsВҰ116215 had been wearing, as well as the collars that had been around theirВҰ116223 camels' necksВҰ116222.
\v 27 ThenВҰ116225 Gideon made \add @the gold\add* into an idol\f + \fr 8:27 \ft We don't really know what вҖҳefodвҖҷ means in this context. (It was also used to refer to priestly clothing.)\f* and placedВҰ116229 it in his \add home\add* cityВҰ116231 of OphrahВҰ116232, and the IsraelisВҰ116234 prostitutedВҰ116233 themselves to it thereВҰ116238, and so it became like a trap for Gideon and his householdВҰ116241.
\rem /s1 Gideon's Death
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ116244\add* MidianВҰ116245 was \add вүҲkept under control by the IsraelisВҰ116248\add* and theyВҰ116250 didn'tВҰ116249 continue to \add вүҲoppress the peopleВҰ116247\add*, and there was peaceВҰ116253 inВҰ116257 the region for fortyВҰ116255 years during Gideon'sВҰ116258 timeВҰ116257.
\s1 The death of Gideon
\rem /s1 The Death of Gideon; Death of Gideon
\p
\v 29 Then \add GideonВҰ116262\add* (Yoash'sВҰ116265 son, \add also known as\add* Yerub-Baal) wentВҰ116261 back and lived inВҰ116267 his houseВҰ116267,
\v 30 andВҰ116269 \add *he\add* fathered seventyВҰ116271 sonsВҰ116272 because he had many wivesВҰ116277.
\v 31 HeВҰ116293 \add also\add* had a mistress inВҰ116284 ShekemВҰ116284вҖ”she also bore him a son that he named AbimelekВҰ116296.
\v 32 GideonВҰ116299 diedВҰ116298 at a goodВҰ116304 old age andВҰ116305 was buriedВҰ116305 inВҰ116303 the tombВҰ116306 of YoashВҰ116302 his fatherВҰ116308, at OfrahВҰ116307 of the \add #Abiezerites\add*.
\p
\v 33 \add вүҲHowever\add* afterВҰ116322 GideonВҰ116317 had diedВҰ116316, the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ116320\add* turnedВҰ116318 away againВҰ116318 \add from Yahweh\add* and prostitutedВҰ116321 themselves to the BaalsВҰ116323вҖ”making Baal-BeritВҰ116327 for themselves as a godВҰ116328.
\v 34 \add *They\add* \add вүҲforgot aboutВҰ116344\add* their godВҰ116337 YahwehВҰ116336вҖ”the one who had rescuedВҰ116338 them from the \add вүҲclutch\add* of all of their enemiesВҰ116343 all around.
\v 35 TheyВҰ116353 didn'tВҰ116346 \add вүҲshow lasting loyaltyВҰ116349\add* to Gideon'sВҰ116354 \add вүҲfamily, despite\add* all the goodВҰ116357 thatВҰ116358 he'd done within YisraelВҰ116362.
\c 9
\s1 Abimelek snatches the kingship
\rem /s1 Abimelech; Abimelech and his successors; Abimelech Rules over Shechem; Abimelech Attempts to Establish a Monarchy
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* Gideon's son AbimelekВҰ116366 wentВҰ116365 to ShekemВҰ116370 to his mother's brothersВҰ116373 and spokeВҰ116375 to \add @those uncles\add* and to all the \add вүҲextended\add* family of his mother's fatherВҰ116384, saying,
\v 2 вҖңPlease \add вүҲask around\add* all the citizensВҰ116394 of ShekemВҰ116395: вҖҳWhat is better for you: Gideon's seventyВҰ116402 sons ruling over you, or having a single man \add вүҲinВҰ116391 charge\add*?вҖҷ Remember that I'm your fleshВҰ116421 and bone.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSo his uncles working\add* onВҰ116430 his behalf, passed that onto all the citizensВҰ116433 of ShekemВҰ116434, and \add вүҲthey became convinced inВҰ116430\add* AbimelekВҰ116443, because they saidВҰ116445, вҖңHe's our brotherВҰ116446.вҖқ
\v 4 ThenВҰ116449 they gaveВҰ116449 him seventyВҰ116452 silverВҰ116453 coins from the templeВҰ116454 of BaalВҰ116458-BerithВҰ116462, andВҰ116449 AbimelekВҰ116465 \add вүҲused them to entice some rough lay-abouts to work for\add* him.
\v 5 ThenВҰ116472 \add #they\add* wentВҰ116472 to his father'sВҰ116475 houseВҰ116473 at OfrahВҰ116476, andВҰ116472 he killedВҰ116477 his seventyВҰ116484 \add half-\add*brothers (Gideon's sonsВҰ116481) there on one stoneВҰ116491. ButВҰ116472 Gideon's youngest son Yotam survivedВҰ116493 because he had hidden \add from them\add*.
\v 6 Then all of the \add prominent\add* citizensВҰ116506 of Shekem and all of Beyt-MilloВҰ116511 assembled themselves, and they wentВҰ116512 and installed AbimelekВҰ116516 as kingВҰ116517 beside an oak treeВҰ116520 near the standing pillar\f + \fr 9:6 \ft Likely connected with idol worship.\f* thatВҰ116521 was inВҰ116523 Shekem.
\s1 Yotam's tree parable
\rem /s1 Jotham's Parable; The Parable of the Trees
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ116525\add* they told Yotam, he wentВҰ116527 and stoodВҰ116528 onВҰ116529 the top of MtВҰ116530. GerizimВҰ116532 and shouted out to them all \add вүҲinВҰ116529 a loud voiceВҰ116534\add*, вҖңListen to me, citizensВҰ116540 of ShekemВҰ116541, so GodВҰ116544 will listen to all of you.
\v 8 Once the treesВҰ116548 wentВҰ116547 about in order to appoint a kingВҰ116551 for themselvesВҰ116550, \add вүҲSo\add* they saidВҰ116552 to the \em oliveВҰ116553 treeВҰ116553\em*, вҖҳReign over us.вҖҷ
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ116558\add* the oliveВҰ116560 treeВҰ116560 replied to them, вҖҳHave I stopped producing my \add вүҲvaluable oilВҰ116564 used to\add* honourВҰ116568 godsВҰ116569 andВҰ116558 menВҰ116570, thatВҰ116565 I should goВҰ116571 to sway above the \add other\add* treesВҰ116575?вҖҷ
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ116577\add* the treesВҰ116578 saidВҰ116577 to the \em figВҰ116579 treeВҰ116579\em*, вҖҳYou comeВҰ116580 \add andВҰ116577\add* reignВҰ116583 over us.вҖҷ
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ116586\add* the figВҰ116588 treeВҰ116588 \add answered\add* them, вҖҳHave I stopped producing my sweetnessВҰ116592 andВҰ116586 my goodВҰ116596 fruitВҰ116595, that I should goВҰ116597 to sway above the \add other\add* treesВҰ116601?вҖҷ
\v 12 ThenВҰ116603 the treesВҰ116604 saidВҰ116603 to the grapevineВҰ116605, вҖҳYou comeВҰ116606 \add andВҰ116603\add* reignВҰ116609 over us.вҖҷ
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ116613\add* the vineВҰ116615 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖҳHave I stopped producing my new wine, whichВҰ116620 cheersВҰ116620 godsВҰ116621 andВҰ116613 man, thatВҰ116620 I should goВҰ116623 to sway over the \add other\add* treesВҰ116627?вҖҷ
\v 14 ThenВҰ116629 all the treesВҰ116632 saidВҰ116629 to the thornbushВҰ116635, вҖҳ\em You\em* comeВҰ116636 \add andВҰ116629\add* reignВҰ116638 over us!вҖҷ
\v 15 The thornbush told the treesВҰ116646, вҖҳIf you all are \add вүҲreally wanted to anointВҰ116650\add* me as kingВҰ116652 over you, comeВҰ116654 \add andВҰ116642\add* takeВҰ116655 refugeВҰ116655 inВҰ116648 \em my\em* shadeВҰ116656. ButВҰ116642 if \add вүҲyou all don'tВҰ116659\add*, may the thornbush send out fireВҰ116661 to \add вүҲburn up\add* Lebanon'sВҰ116669 cedarВҰ116668 \add forests\add*.вҖҷ
\p
\v 16 вҖң\add вүҲTherefore did\add* you all act withВҰ116674 honesty and integrityВҰ116675 when you installed AbimelekВҰ116680 as kingВҰ116677? Did you all treat \add вүҲGideon's family\add* well, and did you all \add вүҲrepay him appropriately for what he did for you all\add*?
\v 17 My fatherВҰ116701 foughtВҰ116700 on your behalf, and even \add вүҲriskedВҰ116703\add* his lifeВҰ116706 out frontВҰ116707 when he \add вүҲrescued you all from the Midianites\add*,
\v 18 \add вүҲbutВҰ116713\add* today you've all risenВҰ116714 up against my father'sВҰ116718 family andВҰ116713 killedВҰ116720 his sonsВҰ116723вҖ”seventyВҰ116724 men on one stoneВҰ116728. ThenВҰ116713 you've installed AbimelekВҰ116733, the son of his femaleВҰ116736 servant, as kingВҰ116730 over the citizensВҰ116739 of ShekemВҰ116740 because he's yourВҰ116742 brotherВҰ116742.
\v 19 \add вүҲNow\add* if you've all actedВҰ116749 with honesty and integrityВҰ116748 with towards \add вүҲGideonВҰ116752 and his family\add* today, be happy with AbimelekВҰ116759, and he'll also be happy with all of you,
\v 20 \add вүҲbutВҰ116766\add* if not, thenВҰ116766 fire will come out of AbimelekВҰ116771 and destroy the citizens of Shekem and Beyt-Millo. Fire will also come out from the Shekem's citizens and from Beyt-Millo, and it'll destroy AbimelechВҰ116790.вҖқ
\v 21 ThenВҰ116792 Yotam fled away and escaped and wentВҰ116795 to Be'er and settled thereВҰ116798 away from the presence of his \add half-\add*brother AbimelekВҰ116800.
\rem /s1 Shechem's Revolt against Abimelech; The Downfall of Abimelech
\p
\v 22 AbimelekВҰ116805 ruledВҰ116804 over YisraelВҰ116808 for threeВҰ116809 yearsВҰ116810,
\v 23 thenВҰ116812 GodВҰ116813 sentВҰ116812 an evilВҰ116815 spiritВҰ116814 between \add *him\add* andВҰ116812 the citizens of ShekemВҰ116820, \add вүҲso\add* the citizens \add *there\add* dealtВҰ116821 treacherouslyВҰ116821 withВҰ116825 AbimelekВҰ116817.
\v 24 The violentВҰ116828 treatment of \add вүҲGideon's\add* seventyВҰ116829 sonsВҰ116830 \add вүҲkept getting brought up\add*, and by \add вүҲit was all blamed on\add* their brotherВҰ116838 AbimelechВҰ116837 who had killedВҰ116840 them, and on \add those of\add* Shekem's citizensВҰ116843 who \add вүҲassisted him in\add* the killing of his brothersВҰ116854.
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ116856\add* the ShekemВҰ116859 citizensВҰ116858 placed men inВҰ116872 ambushВҰ116860 along the tops of the hills \add вүҲto get him\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ116856\add* they robbedВҰ116864 everyoneВҰ116866 who went passedВҰ116870 them along the roadВҰ116872, andВҰ116856 \add so\add* it was reportedВҰ116873 to AbimelechВҰ116865.
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ116889 GaalВҰ116878 (Ebed'sВҰ116881 son) cameВҰ116877 along withВҰ116884 his brothersВҰ116882 and \add вүҲmoved into\add* ShekemВҰ116884, and the citizensВҰ116888 \add *there\add* \add began to\add* trustВҰ116885 \add #them\add*.
\v 27 They went out into the fieldВҰ116892, and they picked grapesВҰ116893 from their vineyardsВҰ116896 and pressed them. They celebrated harvest festivals and they went into the houseВҰ116901 of their gods, thenВҰ116891 they ateВҰ116903 and drankВҰ116904, and they cursedВҰ116905 AbimelekВҰ116908.
\v 28 ThenВҰ116910 GaalВҰ116912 (Ebed'sВҰ116915 son) saidВҰ116910, вҖңWho's Abimelek, and who's Shekem, that we should serve him? Isn't \add @Abimelek\add* \add вүҲGideon's\add* son, and ZebulВҰ116928 is his deputyВҰ116929? Serve the descendants of Shekem's fatherВҰ116935 HamorВҰ116934, \add вүҲbutВҰ116910\add* why should we serve \add @Abimelek\add*?
\v 29 Who will \add вүҲfight withВҰ116947 me to defeat those\add* peopleВҰ116945 and depose Abimelek? ThenВҰ116941 he saidВҰ116952 to Abimelek, вҖҳ\add вүҲGather\add* your army and comeВҰ116956 \add вүҲand fight\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 30 WhenВҰ116958 ZebulВҰ116959, the prince of the cityВҰ116962, heard \add вүҲwhat Ga'alВҰ116966 (Ebed'sВҰ116969 son) had said\add*, \add вүҲhe got very angry\add*
\v 31 and he sentВҰ116973 messengersВҰ116974 to AbimelekВҰ116977 inВҰ116978 secret, saying, вҖңListen, Ebed'sВҰ116984 son GaalВҰ116981 and his brothersВҰ116985 are comingВҰ116986 to ShekemВҰ116987, and wowВҰ116988, they're inciting the cityВҰ116992 againstВҰ116993 you.
\v 32 You and the peopleВҰ116999 who are withВҰ117004 you \add вүҲshould go out atВҰ117004 nightВҰ116997\add* and lie in ambush in the countrysideВҰ117004.
\v 33 ThenВҰ117006 \add вүҲwhen the sunВҰ117009 risesВҰ117008\add* in the morningВҰ117007, you all should set out earlyВҰ117010 and spread out in an attack againstВҰ117023 the cityВҰ117014. Keep watch, then when \add @Ga'al\add* and the peopleВҰ117018 withВҰ117007 him are coming out toward you \add to fight\add*, then you \add can overpower them and\add* \add вүҲtreat him however you think fit\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲSo\add* AbimelekВҰ117032 and all the peopleВҰ117035 with him \add вүҲwent out in the nightВҰ117039\add* and theyВҰ117040 set up fourВҰ117044 units in an ambush against ShekemВҰ117043.
\v 35 \add In the morning,\add* Ga'al (Ebed'sВҰ117051 son) wentВҰ117047 out and he stood at the entranceВҰ117053 of the cityВҰ117055 gateВҰ117054. ThenВҰ117047 AbimelekВҰ117057 and \add вүҲhis men stood up from their hiding places\add*.
\v 36 \add вүҲWhenВҰ117066\add* Ga'al saw the people, he said to ZebulВҰ117075, вҖңLook, a group of people is comingВҰ117079 down from the tops of the hills!вҖқ
\p вҖңYou are seeingВҰ117089 the shadowВҰ117086 of the hills as menВҰ117090,вҖқ Zebul \add вүҲrespondedВҰ117072\add*.
\p
\v 37 \add вүҲButВҰ117093\add* Ga'al said againВҰ117094, вҖңLook, groups of peopleВҰ117100 are coming down from beside the \add вүҲtop of the hill\add*, and \add вүҲanother group\add* is coming from the way of the вҖҳoak of the divinersвҖҷ.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 ThenВҰ117113 ZebulВҰ117115 said to him, вҖң\add вүҲWell, you were the one who\add* said, вҖҳWho is AbimelekВҰ117122 thatВҰ117128 we should serveВҰ117124 him?вҖҷ Aren't these the peopleВҰ117127 who you \add вүҲwere scorning\add*? Indeed now, goВҰ117131 out andВҰ117113 fightВҰ117135 against \add #them\add*.вҖқ
\v 39 \add вүҲSo\add* Ga'al wentВҰ117139 out inВҰ117145 frontВҰ117141 of Shekem's citizensВҰ117142 and foughtВҰ117144 againstВҰ117145 AbimelekВҰ117145.
\v 40 AbimelekВҰ117148 pursuedВҰ117147 him, andВҰ117147 he \add вүҲhad to flee away from him\add*. Many \add of their men\add* fell fatallyВҰ117152 woundedВҰ117152 as far as the entranceВҰ117156 of the city gateВҰ117157.
\v 41 ThenВҰ117159 AbimelekВҰ117160 settled in ArumahВҰ117161, \add вүҲbutВҰ117159\add* ZebulВҰ117163 droveВҰ117162 Ga'alВҰ117166 andВҰ117159 his brothersВҰ117169 away from livingВҰ117170 in ShekemВҰ117171.
\p
\v 42 Now it so happened that the next dayВҰ117174, the peopleВҰ117176 \add of Shekem\add* wentВҰ117175 out into the countrysideВҰ117177, andВҰ117173 \add вүҲit was reportedВҰ117178\add* to AbimelekВҰ117179.
\v 43 SoВҰ117181 he tookВҰ117181 \add вүҲhis men\add* and split them into threeВҰ117186 units. ThenВҰ117181 he waited in ambush in the countrysideВҰ117189. WhenВҰ117182 he sawВҰ117190 and wow, the peopleВҰ117192 were goingВҰ117193 out of the cityВҰ117196, thenВҰ117181 he \add вүҲattackedВҰ117199\add* and killedВҰ117199 them.
\v 44 AbimelekВҰ117201 and the units thatВҰ117203 were with him had spread out and they stoodВҰ117206 at the entranceВҰ117207 of the cityВҰ117209 gateВҰ117208, and twoВҰ117210 units spread out against everyone who was in the fieldВҰ117218 and killedВҰ117219 them.
\v 45 AbimelekВҰ117221 \add вүҲspent thatВҰ117234 whole day attacking Shekem\add*. He capturedВҰ117227 the city and \add #they\add* killedВҰ117237 the peopleВҰ117233 who were inВҰ117223 it. ThenВҰ117221 he tore \add *it\add* down, and scattered salt onВҰ117223 \add @the land\add*.
\p
\v 46 When all the lords of the towerВҰ117250 of ShekemВҰ117252 heardВҰ117246, they wentВҰ117253 into the citadel of the temple for El-BeritВҰ117259,
\v 47 \add вүҲbutВҰ117261\add* itВҰ117261 was reported to AbimelekВҰ117262 that all the lords of the ShekemВҰ117270 towerВҰ117268 had gatheredВҰ117264 there.
\v 48 SoВҰ117272 AbimelekВҰ117273 and all the people with him, went up to MtВҰ117274. TsalmonВҰ117276. \add *He\add* tookВҰ117284 axesВҰ117288 and cut a branchВҰ117291 down from the trees, thenВҰ117272 liftedВҰ117293 it onto his shoulderВҰ117297 and saidВҰ117298 to the people who were with him, вҖң\add вүҲWhat I just did, you all quickly do the same\add*.вҖқ
\v 49 SoВҰ117312 all the people also each cut off a branchВҰ117319 and thenВҰ117312 \add вүҲfollowedВҰ117320\add* AbimelekВҰ117322. They piled them onВҰ117332 top of the underground chamber, \add вүҲand that's how\add* they burnt out the underground chamber. As a result, all the distinguished people inВҰ117332 the towerВҰ117338 of ShekemВҰ117340 also diedвҖ”aboutВҰ117341 a thousandВҰ117341 men and womenВҰ117343.
\p
\v 50 Then AbimelekВҰ117347 wentВҰ117346 to Tebets and set up camp around \add *the city\add* and capturedВҰ117353 it.
\v 51 \add вүҲButВҰ117355\add* thereВҰ117363 was a strong tower in the middleВҰ117359 of the city, so all of the men and the womenВҰ117367 and all the prominent citizensВҰ117369 fled to it. \add вүҲOnce they were all in, they barricaded it up\add* and they went up onto the tower roof.
\v 52 ThenВҰ117379 AbimelekВҰ117380 \add and his men\add* approachedВҰ117386 the tower and foughtВҰ117384 against it, and he cameВҰ117379 in as close as the tower entranceВҰ117389 in order to \add вүҲset fireВҰ117392 to it\add*,
\v 53 \add вүҲbutВҰ117394\add* a womanВҰ117395 threwВҰ117394 an upperВҰ117398 millstone down onto Abimelek'sВҰ117404 headВҰ117401 andВҰ117403 it crushedВҰ117403 his skullВҰ117406.\x + \xo 9:53: \xt 2Sam 11:21.\x*
\v 54 ThenВҰ117408 he cried out hurriedly to the young man bearing his armourВҰ117415, вҖңDraw out your swordВҰ117419 andВҰ117408 put me to death, \add вүҲbecause I don't want it to be said afterwards that I was killedВҰ117426 by\add* a womanВҰ117425.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ117408\add* his young man stabbed him so that he died.
\v 55 \add вүҲWhenВҰ117431\add* the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ117434 warriors\add* sawВҰ117431 that AbimelekВҰ117437 was deadВҰ117436, theyВҰ117431 all returned to their own homes.
\p
\v 56 Thus GodВҰ117443 avenged the evilВҰ117445 of AbimelekВҰ117446 thatВҰ117447 he had done to his fatherВҰ117449 \add Gideon\add* by killingВҰ117450 his seventyВҰ117453 brothersВҰ117454,
\v 57 and GodВҰ117463 \add вүҲcaused all the evilВҰ117459 done by Shekem's menВҰ117460\add* to return back upon theirВҰ117464 own headsВҰ117464, and the curseВҰ117467 of \add вүҲGideon's\add* \add youngest\add* son Yotam, cameВҰ117465 true onВҰ117464 them.
\c 10
\s1 Tola
\rem /s1 Tola Becomes Israel's Judge; Tola and Jair; Tola
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* afterВҰ117475 AbimelekВҰ117476, TolaВҰ117481 (the son of PuahВҰ117484, the son of DodoВҰ117487, \add вүҲfrom the tribe\add* of Yissakar) \add вүҲcame onВҰ117493 the scene\add* to rescue YisraelВҰ117480. He settled in ShamirВҰ117493, in the hill countryВҰ117494 of EfrayimВҰ117495.
\v 2 He \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ117500 for twenty-three years, thenВҰ117497 he diedВҰ117504 andВҰ117497 was buriedВҰ117505 inВҰ117506 ShamirВҰ117506.
\s1 Yair
\rem /s1 Jair Becomes Israel's Judge; Jair
\p
\v 3 AfterВҰ117514 himВҰ117510, YairВҰ117511 the GileaditeВҰ117512 \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ117516 for twenty-two years.
\v 4 He had thirty sonsВҰ117525 thatВҰ117542 rode on thirty donkeysВҰ117530. There were thirty citiesВҰ117532 for them in the GileadВҰ117544 regionВҰ117543 whichВҰ117542 they call Yair'sВҰ117538 villagesВҰ117537 to this dayВҰ117540.
\v 5 ThenВҰ117546 YairВҰ117547 diedВҰ117546 andВҰ117548 heВҰ117548 was buriedВҰ117548 inВҰ117549 KamonВҰ117549.
\s1 The making again of bad of Israelis
\rem /s1 Oppression by the Ammonites; The Ammonites Oppress Israel; Jephthah
\p
\v 6 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ117555\add* continued to do \add вүҲwhat Yahweh considered evil\add*: they worshipped the Ba'als, the Ashtorets, the gods of AramВҰ117570, the gods of SidonВҰ117574, the gods of MoabВҰ117578, the gods of the sons of AmmonВҰ117583, and the gods of the PhilistinesВҰ117586. They forsook Yahweh and didn'tВҰ117591 serveВҰ117560 him.
\v 7 YahwehВҰ117597 \add вүҲwas very angry withВҰ117598\add* YisraelВҰ117598, so he \add вүҲallowed the PhilistinesВҰ117602 andВҰ117594 the AmmonitesВҰ117605 to harass them\add*.
\v 8 They shatteredВҰ117607 andВҰ117607 oppressed the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* thatВҰ117629 yearВҰ117613, \add вүҲbutВҰ117607 it went on\add* for eighteenВҰ117615 years for all the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* who were on the opposite side of the YordanВҰ117626 in the land of the AmoritesВҰ117628, whichВҰ117629 is in the GileadВҰ117630.
\v 9 ThenВҰ117632 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117635\add* also crossedВҰ117632 over the YordanВҰ117638 to fightВҰ117639 against YehudahВҰ117642, against BenyaminВҰ117643, andВҰ117632 against the \add вүҲhalf-tribe\add* of EfrayimВҰ117645.
\p This caused incredible distressВҰ117646 for the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*
\v 10 \add вүҲso\add* \add *they\add* criedВҰ117650 out to YahwehВҰ117655, вҖңWe have sinnedВҰ117657 against you, becauseВҰ117659 we have abandonedВҰ117660 our godВҰ117663 andВҰ117650 we have servedВҰ117664 the Ba'als.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңWasn't it from the Egyptians,вҖқ YahwehВҰ117671 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ117670\add*, вҖңfrom the AmoritesВҰ117680, from the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117684\add*, from the PhilistinesВҰ117687,
\v 12 the Sidonians and AmalekВҰ117690 and MaonВҰ117691, when theyВҰ117692 oppressedВҰ117692 you that you criedВҰ117694 out to me, and I \add вүҲrescued you all from them\add*?
\v 13 \add вүҲYet\add* you've all abandonedВҰ117701 me andВҰ117703 servedВҰ117703 otherВҰ117705 godsВҰ117704. Therefore, I won'tВҰ117707 not continue to rescue you.
\v 14 Go andВҰ117714 cryВҰ117714 out to the gods thatВҰ117718 you've all chosenВҰ117719 for yourselves. They shouldВҰ117722 deliverВҰ117722 you all atВҰ117720 the timeВҰ117724 of yourВҰ117725 distressВҰ117725.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ117727 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ117730\add* saidВҰ117727 to YahwehВҰ117733, вҖңWe've sinnedВҰ117734. You do to us accordingВҰ117739 to all that is goodВҰ117741 inВҰ117742 yourВҰ117742 eyesВҰ117742. Only pleaseВҰ117745 rescue us today.вҖқ
\v 16 They removedВҰ117749 the foreignВҰ117753 godsВҰ117752 from amongВҰ117754 them, and they worshipped YahwehВҰ117758 and \add вүҲso he becameВҰ117759 concerned\add* withВҰ117761 Yisrael'sВҰ117762 suffering.
\p
\v 17 Now the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117767 had assembledВҰ117770\add* and were camped inВҰ117769 GileadВҰ117769. So the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ117772\add* gatheredВҰ117770 together and they camped atВҰ117769 Mitspah.
\v 18 ThenВҰ117776 the princes of Gilead saidВҰ117776 to \add вүҲeach other\add*, вҖңWho \add вүҲwill lead us\add* to fightВҰ117788 againstВҰ117789 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117790\add*? He can becomeВҰ117791 the leaderВҰ117778 over all of us who live inВҰ117789 Gilead.вҖқ
\c 11
\s1 Yiftah
\rem /s1 Jephthah and his successors; Jephthah Becomes Israel's Judge; Jephthah
\p
\v 1 NowВҰ117798 YiftahВҰ117812 the GileaditeВҰ117799 was a fierce warrior, \add вүҲbutВҰ117798\add* he was a \add вүҲprostitute'sВҰ117807\add* son and his fatherВҰ117808 was GileadВҰ117809.
\v 2 Gilead'sВҰ117817 wife also gave birthВҰ117814 to sons for him, and \add when\add* those sons of the wife grew up, they droveВҰ117824 YiftahВҰ117827 out and told him, вҖңYouВҰ117825 won'tВҰ117830 \add вүҲget any inheritanceВҰ117832 from our father'sВҰ117835 estate\add* because you're a son of anotherВҰ117840 woman.вҖқ
\v 3 SoВҰ117843 Yiftah fled from the presence of his \add half-\add*brothers and heВҰ117843 settled in the TobВҰ117849 regionВҰ117848. Unprincipled menВҰ117854 associated around Yiftah and wentВҰ117856 around with him.
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSome timeВҰ117861 later\add*, the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117865 battled against\add* YisraelВҰ117868.
\v 5 andВҰ117870 \add вүҲthat was when\add* the eldersВҰ117881 of GileadВҰ117882 wentВҰ117880 to summon YiftahВҰ117886 from the TobВҰ117888 regionВҰ117887.
\v 6 ThenВҰ117890 \add вүҲrequested\add* YiftahВҰ117891, вҖңCome andВҰ117890 be our commanderВҰ117895 so weВҰ117896 can fightВҰ117896 againstВҰ117897 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117898\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖңDon't you all hateВҰ117906 me? YiftahВҰ117901 asked \add *them\add*. вҖңDidn't you yourselves driveВҰ117908 me out of my father'sВҰ117910 houseВҰ117909? \add вүҲSoВҰ117900\add* why have you all comeВҰ117912 to me now when you have \add #troubles\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add вүҲWell, true\add*,вҖқ the Gilead eldersВҰ117920 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add ButВҰ117919\add* now we've turned back to you. \add вүҲSoВҰ117919 join\add* withВҰ117932 us and fightВҰ117931 againstВҰ117932 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117933\add*, and you'll becomeВҰ117934 commander over all of who lives inВҰ117932 Gilead.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңIf you bringВҰ117949 me back to fightВҰ117952 againstВҰ117953 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ117954\add*,вҖқ YiftahВҰ117942 \add вүҲasked\add* \add *them\add*, вҖңandВҰ117941 if YahwehВҰ117956 \add вүҲhelps me defeat them\add*, \add is it correct that\add* I'llВҰ117960 actually becomeВҰ117960 your leader?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңYahwehВҰ117971 will be a witness betweenВҰ117974 us,вҖқ the GileadВҰ117967 eldersВҰ117965 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ117964\add*, вҖң\add вүҲthat we'll most certainly do what youВҰ117978 just saidВҰ117964\add*.вҖқ
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ117982\add* Yiftah wentВҰ117982 withВҰ118003 the GileadВҰ117987 eldersВҰ117986, and the peopleВҰ117989 set himВҰ117990 as commanderВҰ117993 and leader over themselves. (Yiftah had spokenВҰ117994 all those wordsВҰ118000 before YahwehВҰ118002 atВҰ118003 Mitspah.)
\p
\v 12 Then YiftahВҰ118007 sentВҰ118006 messengersВҰ118008 to the \add вүҲAmmonite\add* kingВҰ118011, demanding, вҖңWhat's happened withВҰ118025 respect to me and to you, that you'veВҰ118022 comeВҰ118022 againstВҰ118025 me to fightВҰ118024 over my land?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 The \add вүҲAmmonite\add* kingВҰ118028 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ118027\add* to Yiftah's messengersВҰ118034, вҖңBecause \add вүҲthe Israelis\add* seized my land \add вүҲwhen theyВҰ118043 cameВҰ118043\add* out of EgyptВҰ118044. It wentВҰ118043 from the ArnonВҰ118045 \add river\add* up to the YabbokВҰ118048 \add river\add*, andВҰ118027 over to the YordanВҰ118051 \add river\add*. Now return \add @the land\add* peaceablyВҰ118055.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ118057 Yiftah sentВҰ118060 messengersВҰ118061 back to the \add вүҲAmmonite\add* kingВҰ118064
\v 15 to tell him, вҖңYiftahВҰ118072 \add вүҲwants you to know that\add* YisraelВҰ118076 didn'tВҰ118073 take land from MoabВҰ118080 nor from \add вүҲyou AmmonitesВҰ118085\add*.
\v 16 However inВҰ118088 their coming up from EgyptВҰ118089, YisraelВҰ118091 wentВҰ118090 through the wildernessВҰ118092 as far as the \add вүҲRed Sea\add* until arriving atВҰ118088 KadeshВҰ118099.
\v 17 WhenВҰ118101 Yisrael \add (IsraelВҰ118102)\add* sent messengersВҰ118103 to the king of Edom, saying, вҖҳPlease may \add #we\add* pass through your land,вҖҷ the king of Edom wouldn't listenВҰ118116. \add @Yisrael\add* likewise sent to the king of MoabВҰ118123, butВҰ118101 he wasn't willingВҰ118126 \add either\add*, so Yisrael stayed atВҰ118114 KadeshВҰ118129.\x + \xo 11:17: \xt Num 20:14-21.\x*
\v 18 ThenВҰ118131 \add #we\add* went through the wildernessВҰ118132 and turned away from the land of EdomВҰ118137 and the land of Moab, thenВҰ118131 went \add the long way\add* \add вүҲaroundВҰ118133 the eastern border\add* of Moab. They campedВҰ118148 onВҰ118132 the otherВҰ118149 side of the Arnon \add river\add*, butВҰ118131 they didn'tВҰ118151 go within Moab'sВҰ118141 borders, because the Arnon was the border of Moab.\x + \xo 11:18: \xt Num 21:4.\x*
\v 19 YisraelВҰ118162 sent messengersВҰ118163 to the AmoriteВҰ118169 KingВҰ118167 SihonВҰ118166, the king of HeshbonВҰ118171 \add вүҲandВҰ118161 asked\add* him, вҖҳPleaseВҰ118174, let us pass through your land as far as \add #our\add* placeВҰ118181.вҖҷ\x + \xo 11:19-22: \xt Num 21:21-24.\x*
\v 20 ButВҰ118183 \add King\add* SihonВҰ118186 didn'tВҰ118183 trustВҰ118185 Yisrael passing through within his border, \add вүҲso\add* \add *he\add* assembled all of his peopleВҰ118198 together and they camped atВҰ118191 Jahaz, and he battled withВҰ118191 Yisrael.
\v 21 ThenВҰ118206 Yisrael'sВҰ118210 godВҰ118208, YahwehВҰ118207, handed \add King\add* SihonВҰ118213 and all his peopleВҰ118218 over to Yisrael and \add вүҲwe\add* defeatedВҰ118221 them. Thus Yisrael tookВҰ118222 possessionВҰ118222 of all of the land of the AmoritesВҰ118228 inhabiting that regionВҰ118227вҖ”
\v 22 everything within the AmoriteВҰ118238 territoryВҰ118237 from the ArnonВҰ118239 \add river\add* to the YabbokВҰ118242, andВҰ118233 from the wildernessВҰ118245 as far as the JordanВҰ118248.
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ118250\add* since it was Yisrael'sВҰ118254 godВҰ118253 YahwehВҰ118251 that expelled the AmoritesВҰ118258 out of the presence of his peopleВҰ118260 Yisrael, \add вүҲdo you actually think that you can takeВҰ118263\add* it \add now\add*?
\v 24 Wouldn't you take possession if your god ChemoshВҰ118269, allowed you to? \add вүҲSo\add* \add too\add* all that ourВҰ118280 godВҰ118270 YahwehВҰ118278 has dispossessedВҰ118277 ahead of us, we'll possess that.
\v 25 Are you reallyВҰ118285 betterВҰ118285 now than Zippor'sВҰ118291 son, KingВҰ118292 BalakВҰ118288 of MoabВҰ118293? Did he dare contend withВҰ118303 YisraelВҰ118298 or did he ever wage war againstВҰ118303 them?\x + \xo 11:25: \xt Num 22:1-6.\x*
\v 26 YisraelВҰ118306 livedВҰ118305 in HeshbonВҰ118307 and in its villages for threeВҰ118319 hundredВҰ118320 years, and in AroerВҰ118309 and in its villages, and in all the citiesВҰ118313 that are along the banks of the ArnonВҰ118318вҖ”\add вүҲso\add* why didn'tВҰ118323 you repossess \add <them\add* during that timeВҰ118326?
\v 27 I haven't \add вүҲdone anything wrong to\add* you, \add вүҲbutВҰ118329\add* you're doingВҰ118335 wrong inВҰ118339 dealing withВҰ118339 me by fighting againstВҰ118339 me. YahwehВҰ118341, the judge, will decide today between the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ118346\add* andВҰ118329 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ118349\add*.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲButВҰ118351\add* the \add вүҲAmmonite\add* kingВҰ118353 didn'tВҰ118351 \add вүҲtake any notice of Yiftah's messageВҰ118358\add* to him.
\rem /s1 Jephthah's Vow
\p
\v 29 Then Yahweh's spiritВҰ118369 \add вүҲempowered\add* YiftahВҰ118368, and he passed through the Gilead and MenashshehВҰ118377, and through MizpahВҰ118381 of Gilead, and from \add *there\add* he passed through the \add вүҲAmmonite region\add*,
\v 30 andВҰ118389 \add *he\add* \add вүҲmade a promise\add* to YahwehВҰ118392, вҖңIfВҰ118390 you reallyВҰ118396 give \add вүҲme victory over the AmmonitesВҰ118401\add*,
\v 31 thenВҰ118404 whoever's \add вүҲthe first person\add* to comeВҰ118407 out of my houseВҰ118409 to meet me when I returnВҰ118411 inВҰ118411 peaceВҰ118412 from the \add вүҲbattle against the AmmonitesВҰ118414\add*, thatВҰ118406 person will belong to YahwehВҰ118416, andВҰ118404 I will offer him up as a whole burntВҰ118418 offeringВҰ118418.вҖқ
\v 32 \add вүҲSo\add* YiftahВҰ118422 \add вүҲwent to the Ammonite territory\add* to fightВҰ118427 againstВҰ118428 them, and YahwehВҰ118433 \add вүҲenabled them to defeat them\add*.
\v 33 ThenВҰ118436 he attacked them from AroerВҰ118437 and as far as \add вүҲthe entranceВҰ118440\add* to MinnithВҰ118443, twentyВҰ118444 cities, and thenВҰ118436 up to AvelВҰ118447-KeramimВҰ118448, \add вүҲslaughtering a hugeВҰ118450 number\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ118436\add* the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ118454\add* were subduedВҰ118452 by the presence of the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ118457\add*.
\s1 Yiftah's daughter
\rem /s1 Jephthah's Daughter
\p
\v 34 \add вүҲWhen\add* Yiftah got back to his houseВҰ118465 inВҰ118470 the MizpahВҰ118462 area, look, his daughter was comingВҰ118468 out to meet him with tambourinesВҰ118470 and with dancingВҰ118471. She was \add &their\add* only childВҰ118474вҖ”he didn'tВҰ118475 have any son or daughter apart from her.
\v 35 WhenВҰ118484 he sawВҰ118485 her, he tore his clothesВҰ118490 and saidВҰ118491, вҖңOh no! MyВҰ118499 daughterВҰ118493! Indeed, you'veВҰ118495 made me bow inВҰ118499 grief, and you'reВҰ118497 amongВҰ118499 thoseВҰ118499 who cause me pain, because I \add вүҲmade a vow\add* to YahwehВҰ118506 and I \add вүҲcan'tВҰ118507 go back onВҰ118499 it\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ118511 she saidВҰ118511 to him, вҖңMy fatherВҰ118513, you'veВҰ118514 \add вүҲmade a vow\add* to Yahweh. Do to me \add вүҲwhatever you promised\add*, afterВҰ118526 what Yahweh has done for youвҖ”total vengeanceВҰ118531 againstВҰ118532 yourВҰ118525 \add вүҲAmmonite\add* enemiesВҰ118532.вҖқ
\v 37 \add вүҲButВҰ118536\add* she \add вүҲasked\add* herВҰ118539 fatherВҰ118539, вҖң\add вүҲJust do this one thingВҰ118542\add* for me: release me for twoВҰ118546 monthsВҰ118547, so I can goВҰ118548 away \add вүҲand take some companionsВҰ118558\add*. I'll fall prostrate on the hills and I'll weep \add вүҲbecause I'll never have a chance to marry\add*.вҖқ
\v 38 He \add вүҲagreed\add* and thenВҰ118561 sentВҰ118563 herВҰ118569 away for twoВҰ118565 monthsВҰ118566. She wentВҰ118567 \add вүҲwith some\add* companionsВҰ118569, and she wept on the hills \add вүҲbecause she'd never be a mother\add*.
\v 39 ThenВҰ118578 atВҰ118602 the end of the twoВҰ118581 monthsВҰ118582, she returnedВҰ118583 to her fatherВҰ118586 andВҰ118578 he carried out his vow withВҰ118602 respect to her \add вүҲso indeed\add* she \add вүҲnever had a chance to marry\add*.
\p \add AfterВҰ118589 thatВҰ118592,\add* it becameВҰ118599 a customВҰ118601 inВҰ118602 YisraelВҰ118602
\v 40 that the \add вүҲyoung women\add* of YisraelВҰ118609 go to commemorateВҰ118610 the daughterВҰ118611 of YiftahВҰ118613 the GileaditeВҰ118614 for four days during the year.
\c 12
\s1 Yiftah and the Efrayimites
\rem /s1 Intertribal Dissension; Jephthah and Ephraim; Jephthah and the Ephraimites; Ephraim Fights with Jephthah
\p
\v 1 Now the men of EfrayimВҰ118622 were summonedВҰ118637 and they passedВҰ118623 northwardВҰ118624 and they saidВҰ118625 to YiftahВҰ118626, вҖңWhy did you passВҰ118629 through inВҰ118632 order to fightВҰ118631 againstВҰ118632 the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ118634\add*, butВҰ118620 you didn'tВҰ118636 call us to goВҰ118638 withВҰ118632 you? We're going to burnВҰ118641 your houseВҰ118640 down over you!вҖқ
\p
\v 2 вҖң\add вүҲI've been involved in very intense disputes\add*вҖ”my peopleВҰ118652 against the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ118655\add*,вҖқ YiftahВҰ118646 told them. вҖңWhenВҰ118645 I summonedВҰ118657 you all, you didn'tВҰ118659 \add come andВҰ118645\add* rescue me from \add вүҲthem\add*.
\v 3 \add вүҲWhenВҰ118665\add* I could see that you weren't coming to assist, I tookВҰ118673 my lifeВҰ118674 into my own handsВҰ118675. I \add вүҲadvanced against\add* the \add вүҲAmmonitesВҰ118680\add*, andВҰ118665 YahwehВҰ118682 gaveВҰ118681 \add вүҲme victory over\add* them. \add вүҲSoВҰ118665\add* why thenВҰ118665 have you all comeВҰ118685 \add вүҲhere\add* to fightВҰ118689 against me today?вҖқ
\v 4 ThenВҰ118692 YiftahВҰ118693 assembled all of the men of Gilead andВҰ118692 \add вүҲthey battled against\add* Efrayim. The men of Gilead struck Efrayim because they had said, вҖң\add вүҲYou Gilead people are just\add* fugitivesВҰ118712 from EfrayimвҖ”\add living here\add* in the middle of Efrayim, in the middle of MenashshehВҰ118719.вҖқ
\v 5 The Gileadites capturedВҰ118721 the crossing places of the Jordan along Efrayim. ThenВҰ118721 when any of the survivors from Efrayim would say, вҖңMay I crossВҰ118733 over,вҖқ the menВҰ118736 of GileadВҰ118722 would \add вүҲask\add*, вҖңAre you an Efrayimite?вҖқ If he said, вҖңNo,вҖқ
\v 6 thenВҰ118745 they'd \add вүҲdemand\add*, вҖң\add вүҲNowВҰ118758\add* say: ShibbolethВҰ118750.вҖқ ButВҰ118745 if he said вҖңSibbolethВҰ118752вҖқ because he \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ118753 have time to think\add* to pronounceВҰ118755 it correctly, they would seizeВҰ118757 him andВҰ118745 would slaughterВҰ118759 him at those crossing places of the YordanВҰ118763. Forty-two thousandВҰ118770 from EfrayimВҰ118767 fell at that time.
\p
\v 7 YiftahВҰ118780 the GileaditeВҰ118781 \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ118776 for sixВҰ118777 yearsВҰ118778, thenВҰ118772 \add *he\add* diedВҰ118779 andВҰ118772 was buriedВҰ118782 among the citiesВҰ118783 of GileadВҰ118784.
\s1 Ibtsan, Elon, and Abdon
\rem /s1 Ibzan, Elon, and Abdon; Ibzan Becomes Israel's Judge; Ibzan, Elon and Abdon
\p
\v 8 Then afterВҰ118788 himВҰ118788, Ibtsan of Bethlehem \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ118791.
\v 9 Now he had thirty sons. He \add вүҲgave\add* away thirty daughters to \add вүҲbe married to outsiders\add*, andВҰ118796 he broughtВҰ118807 in thirty daughters for his sons from the outside. \add @Ibtsan\add* \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ118815 for sevenВҰ118816 yearsВҰ118817,
\v 10 andВҰ118821 \add вүҲwhen\add* \add *he\add* diedВҰ118819, he was buriedВҰ118821 in BethlehemВҰ118820.
\rem /s1 Elon Becomes Israel's Judge
\p
\v 11 After himВҰ118827, ElonВҰ118831 the Zebulunite \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ118830 for tenВҰ118837 yearsВҰ118838.
\v 12 \add вүҲWhenВҰ118840\add* \add *he\add* diedВҰ118840, he was buriedВҰ118843 in Ayyalon in the land of Zebulun.
\rem /s1 Abdon Becomes Israel's Judge
\v 13 After himВҰ118850, AbdonВҰ118854, the son of HillelВҰ118857 the PiratoniteВҰ118858 \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ118853.
\v 14 He had fortyВҰ118863 sons andВҰ118860 thirtyВҰ118865 grandsons, who rode on seventyВҰ118871 young male donkeysВҰ118872. He \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ118876 for eightВҰ118877 yearsВҰ118878.
\v 15 ThenВҰ118880 AbdonВҰ118881 (the son of HillelВҰ118884 the PiratoniteВҰ118885) diedВҰ118880, andВҰ118880 he was buriedВҰ118886 in PiratonВҰ118887 in the land of EfrayimВҰ118889, in the hill countryВҰ118890 of the \add #Amalekites\add*.
\c 13
\s1 Shimshon's birth
\rem /s1 The Birth of Samson; Samson and the Philistines
\p
\v 1 TheВҰ118902 \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ118896\add* continued to do \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ118900 considered as evilВҰ118898\add*, so \add *he\add* \add вүҲallowed the PhilistinesВҰ118905 to oppress them\add* for fortyВҰ118906 years.
\v 2 \add вүҲNow\add* there was a manВҰ118911 named ManoahВҰ118917 from ZorahВҰ118913, of the families of the DanitesВҰ118915. His wife was barrenВҰ118919 \add вүҲso they had no childrenВҰ118921\add*.
\v 3 \add One day,\add* Yahweh's messengerВҰ118924 appearedВҰ118923 to the wife and told her, вҖңListen, pleaseВҰ118934, you are barrenВҰ118937 and \add вүҲhave never\add* given birth, butВҰ118923 you will conceiveВҰ118940 and \add вүҲhave\add* a son.
\v 4 Now take care that you surely don't drink wine or strongВҰ118951 drink, andВҰ118944 that you don't eat anything \add вүҲprohibited by our rules\add*,
\v 5 because you'll definitely become pregnantВҰ118961 and will \add вүҲgive birth to\add* a son. \add вүҲHis hair mustВҰ118961 never be cut\add* because \add *he'll\add* be a NaziriteВҰ118973 to GodВҰ118974 from \add вүҲhis conception\add*. He will beginВҰ118981 to rescue YisraelВҰ118985 from the \add вүҲoppression\add* of the PhilistinesВҰ118987.вҖқ\x + \xo 13:5: \xt Num 6:1-5.\x*
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ118989 the womanВҰ118990 wentВҰ118989 and explained to her husband, вҖңA man of God came to me. \add вүҲHe looked like one of God's messengersВҰ119000\add*вҖ”\add вүҲextremely terrifying\add*вҖ”\add вүҲso\add* I didn't \add like to\add* ask him \add вүҲwhereВҰ119006 he'd come from\add*, and he didn't \add вүҲtell\add* me his name.
\v 7 ThenВҰ119018 he told me, вҖҳYou're definitely pregnantВҰ119021 and you'll \add вүҲgive birth to\add* a son. SoВҰ119018 now, you mustn't drink wine or strongВҰ119030 drink, and you mustn't eat anything \add вүҲprohibited by our rules\add*, because the boy will be a NaziriteВҰ119039 to GodВҰ119040 from \add вүҲconception\add* untilВҰ119046 the dayВҰ119048 of his deathВҰ119049.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 8 Then ManoahВҰ119053 prayedВҰ119052 to YahwehВҰ119059, вҖңOh please, my masterВҰ119059, please let the manВҰ119060 of GodВҰ119061 that you sentВҰ119063 \add before\add*, comeВҰ119064 \add back\add* to us againВҰ119067 so he can instruct us about what we mustВҰ119072 do for this boyВҰ119073 who's going to be born.вҖқ
\v 9 The true God listenedВҰ119076 to Manoah'sВҰ119079 \add вүҲrequest\add*, andВҰ119076 God's messengerВҰ119081 cameВҰ119080 to the womanВҰ119086 againВҰ119083 when sheВҰ119087 was sittingВҰ119088 \add out\add* inВҰ119078 the fieldВҰ119089, \add вүҲbutВҰ119076\add* her husbandВҰ119091 Manoah wasn't withВҰ119078 her,
\v 10 \add вүҲso\add* \add *she\add* quicklyВҰ119095 ran andВҰ119095 told her husband, вҖңLook. The man has appeared \add again\add* who came to me that dayВҰ119109.вҖқ
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ119112\add* ManoahВҰ119114 \add вүҲfollowed\add* his wife, andВҰ119112 \add when\add* he came to the man, he \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңAre you the man who spokeВҰ119127 to \add вүҲmy wife\add* \add before\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* \add вүҲit was me\add*,вҖқ he replied.
\p
\v 12 вҖңNow may yourВҰ119138 wordsВҰ119138 comeВҰ119137 \add вүҲtrue\add*,вҖқ saidВҰ119134 ManoahВҰ119135. вҖң\add вүҲHow should we bring up\add* the boy, andВҰ119145 \add вүҲwhat will his workВҰ119145 be\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add вүҲYou wife mustВҰ119160 carefully follow everything I told her\add*,вҖқ Yahweh's messengerВҰ119148 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 14 вҖңShe mustn't \add вүҲeat or drink\add* anything that comesВҰ119165 from the grapevineВҰ119167. She mustn't drink wine or strongВҰ119171 drink, and she mustn't eat anything \add вүҲprohibited by our rules\add*. She mustВҰ119169 do everything that I've instructedВҰ119184 her.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңPlease \add вүҲstay a little longer\add*,вҖқ ManoahВҰ119188 \add вүҲasked\add* Yahweh's messengerВҰ119191, вҖңso that weВҰ119197 can prepareВҰ119197 a \add вүҲmeal of tender goat meat to honour\add* yourВҰ119198 presence.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңEven if \add вүҲI stayed longer\add*, I wouldn't eatВҰ119213 your \add вүҲfood\add*,вҖқ Yahweh's messenger \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ119202\add* if you \add вүҲwanted to\add* prepare a burntВҰ119218 offeringВҰ119218 for Yahweh, you may offer it.вҖқ (Because ManoahВҰ119207 didn'tВҰ119211 know that \add вүҲthe messenger had come from\add* Yahweh.)
\v 17 вҖңWhat'sВҰ119237 your nameВҰ119239,вҖқ ManoahВҰ119233 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңso that weВҰ119245 can honourВҰ119245 youВҰ119245 when your wordsВҰ119243 comeВҰ119242 \add вүҲtrue\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖңWhy are youВҰ119256 askingВҰ119256 aboutВҰ119257 my nameВҰ119257,вҖқ Yahweh's messengerВҰ119252 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲYou simply couldn't understand\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 Then Manoah got their \add вүҲyoung goat\add* and \add the other requirements for\add* the offeringВҰ119274, and he \add вүҲpresented\add* a sacrifice to Yahweh on the rockВҰ119278. Then \add вүҲan amazing thing happened\add*\f + \fr 13:19 \ft We've changed this to a passive construction here, because it's not specified whether it was Yahweh himself or his messenger who did the miracle.\f* while Manoah and his wife watchedвҖ”
\v 20 when the \add #flames\add* went up into the sky from the altar, Yahweh'sВҰ119295 messengerВҰ119293 went up inВҰ119287 the \add #flames\add* while ManoahВҰ119298 andВҰ119286 his wife were watching. \add вүҲWhenВҰ119286 they saw that,\add* they \add вүҲquickly bowed right down\add* to the groundВҰ119305.
\v 21 \add After that,\add* Manoah andВҰ119307 his wife \add вүҲnever saw him againВҰ119310\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ119307 now\add* Manoah knewВҰ119321 that he was Yahweh's messenger.
\p
\v 22 ManoahВҰ119330 said to his wife, вҖң\add вүҲWe'll definitely die now\add* because we've seen GodВҰ119337!вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ButВҰ119340 his wife replied to him, вҖңIf YahwehВҰ119345 had wanted to killВҰ119346 us, he wouldn't have \add вүҲacceptedВҰ119349\add* the entireВҰ119357 burntВҰ119351 offering and the grainВҰ119352 offering. He wouldn't have shownВҰ119354 us all those things, and he wouldn't have \add вүҲgiven us those instructions\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add In due course,\add* the womanВҰ119366 gaveВҰ119365 birthВҰ119365 to a son and she named him ShimshonВҰ119372 \add (commonly misnamed as вҖҳSamsonвҖҷ in English)\add*. The boyВҰ119374 grew up and YahwehВҰ119376 blessedВҰ119375 him,
\v 25 and thenВҰ119378 Yahweh's spiritВҰ119379 beganВҰ119378 to stir himВҰ119381 \add when he was\add* inВҰ119382 MahanehВҰ119382 DanвҖ”between ZorahВҰ119386 and between EshtaolВҰ119388.
\c 14
\s1 Shimshon and the woman from Timnah
\rem /s1 Samson's Riddle; Samson's Marriage; Samson and the Woman from Timnah
\p
\v 1 \add One time when\add* ShimshonВҰ119392 went to TimnahВҰ119393, he \add вүҲnoticedВҰ119394\add* a young, Philistine womanВҰ119395 \add there\add*,
\v 2 and he went \add вүҲback home\add* and he reported to his \add вүҲparents\add*, вҖңI saw a Philistine woman inВҰ119407 TimnahВҰ119407 \add вүҲthat I'd like you to get for me as my\add* wife.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңIsn't thereВҰ119421 a womanВҰ119427 among your relativesВҰ119423?вҖқ his \add вүҲparents asked\add* him, вҖңOr among all of \add #our\add* peopleВҰ119426? Why take a wife from the uncircumcisedВҰ119435 PhilistinesВҰ119434?вҖқ
\p вҖңGet her for me,вҖқ ShimshonВҰ119437 said to his father, вҖңbecause \add вүҲI feel she's right for me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲNowВҰ119467 hisВҰ119452 parents\add* didn'tВҰ119453 know that YahwehВҰ119456 \add вүҲwas arranging this\add*, because he was seekingВҰ119463 an opportunity againstВҰ119464 the PhilistinesВҰ119464 who were \add вүҲoppressing\add* YisraelВҰ119469 atВҰ119465 that timeВҰ119465.
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ119481 ShimshonВҰ119473 wentВҰ119477 to TimnahВҰ119476 with hisВҰ119475 \add вүҲparents\add* and \add when\add* theyВҰ119477 got to the vineyardsВҰ119480 \add *there\add*, wow, a youngВҰ119483 lionВҰ119483 roared \add вүҲwhen it saw\add* himВҰ119486.
\v 6 Yahweh'sВҰ119491 spiritВҰ119490 \add вүҲrose up in\add* \add @Shimshon\add*, andВҰ119488 he tore \add @the lion\add* to pieces \add вүҲwith his bare hands\add* like butchering a youngВҰ119494 goatВҰ119494, \add вүҲbutВҰ119488\add* he didn'tВҰ119496 \add вүҲmention to his parents\add* what he'd done.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ119511 he \add вүҲcontinued on\add* and talked with the womanВҰ119508, and \add вүҲhe really liked her\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲSomeВҰ119518 timeВҰ119514 later when he returnedВҰ119513 for the wedding\add*, he turnedВҰ119516 off the path to look for the lion's carcass, and \add вүҲto his surprise\add*, a swarmВҰ119522 of bees had nested inВҰ119524 the carcass and \add there was\add* honeyВҰ119526 \add there\add*.
\v 9 He \add вүҲfilled his cupped handsВҰ119531 with honeyВҰ119553\add*, and \add вүҲcontinued\add* alongвҖ”walking and eatingВҰ119534 as he went to \add вүҲwhere his parents were\add*. He even gaveВҰ119542 some to them \add вүҲto try\add*, butВҰ119528 he didn'tВҰ119545 tell them that he had scooped \add *it\add* out of the carcassВҰ119550 of a dead lionВҰ119551.
\v 10 ThenВҰ119555 his fatherВҰ119556 went \add вүҲto visit\add* the womanВҰ119559, andВҰ119560 \add вүҲin the custom of the youngВҰ119567 menВҰ119567\add* \add of the time\add*, ShimshonВҰ119562 \add вүҲheld\add* a party \add thereВҰ119561\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲWhenВҰ119571\add* they sawВҰ119570 him, they brought thirtyВҰ119573 closeВҰ119574 friends to join him.\f + \fr 14:11 \ft Although we can understand the words here, we're not certain of the implications, or perhaps the cultural traditions. Did Shimshon appear too alone? Too intimidating? Or was it just bringing more friends for good food and drink?\f*
\v 12 SamsonВҰ119580 saidВҰ119578 to them, вҖңLet me suggest a riddle for you all. If you're \add able to\add* explain it to me during the sevenВҰ119592 daysВҰ119593 of the party and \add вүҲyou've worked it out correctly\add*, I'llВҰ119596 giveВҰ119596 you all thirty linenВҰ119599 coats and thirty sets of clothesВҰ119599.
\v 13 ButВҰ119604 if you all can'tВҰ119606 \add вүҲexplain it\add* to me, thenВҰ119604 you yourselves mustВҰ119607 giveВҰ119610 me thirty linenВҰ119614 coats andВҰ119604 thirty sets of clothesВҰ119614.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲOkay, we're listening. Tell us the riddleВҰ119621\add*.вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ119624\add* he said,
\q1 вҖңFood came out of the eaterВҰ119626,
\q1 вүҲandВҰ119624 sweetnessВҰ119631 came out of the strongВҰ119629 one.вҖқ
\m ButВҰ119624 threeВҰ119636 daysВҰ119637 later, they \add вүҲstill couldn't solve his\add* riddleВҰ119635.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ119639 onВҰ119665 the seventh day,\f + \fr 14:15 \ft The Greek Septuagint translation says вҖҳthe \+em fourth\+em* dayвҖҷ, which perhaps might fit better into the narrative, but вҖҳseventhвҖҷ is in the Hebrew that we have and not necessarily incorrect.\f* they \add вүҲpressured\add* Shimshon'sВҰ119646 wifeВҰ119644, вҖңGet your husband \add вүҲto tell you the answer of\add* the riddleВҰ119656, otherwise we'll burnВҰ119659 \add down\add* your father' houseВҰ119663 and you \add as well\add*. \add вүҲDid you inviteВҰ119667 us to the party just to impoverishВҰ119666\add* us?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ119671 Shimshon'sВҰ119673 wifeВҰ119672 \add вүҲput on a crying act\add* andВҰ119671 said, вҖңYou mustВҰ119696 hateВҰ119678 meвҖ”you don'tВҰ119679 loveВҰ119680 me \add because\add* you'veВҰ119682 \add вүҲcreated\add* a riddle \add вүҲfor my relatives\add*, yet you haven't \add вүҲeven told me the answer\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖңListen,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңI haven't \add even\add* \add вүҲtold my own parents\add*. Should I tell you?вҖқ
\v 17 She continued to cry beside him throughout the seven-day party, and thenВҰ119698 \add finally\add* on the seventhВҰ119700 day, he \add gave in and\add* told her because she kept nagging him, \add so in the end\add* she \add вүҲwas able to reveal the answer to her relatives\add*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ119721 the menВҰ119723 of the cityВҰ119724 said to \add @Shimshon\add* beforeВҰ119727 the sunВҰ119729 wentВҰ119728 down onВҰ119727 the seventhВҰ119726 dayВҰ119725,
\q1 вҖңWhat is sweeterВҰ119732 than honeyВҰ119733?
\q1 And what's strongerВҰ119735 than a lionВҰ119736?вҖқ
\m \add вүҲSoВҰ119721\add* he said to them,
\q1 вҖңIf you all hadn't ploughed withВҰ119727 my heiferВҰ119741,
\q1 you wouldn't have been able to solve my riddleВҰ119744.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ119746 Yahweh's spiritВҰ119748 \add вүҲrose up in\add* him, and he went to AshkelonВҰ119751 and killedВҰ119752 thirtyВҰ119755 men \add there\add*. He tookВҰ119757 theirВҰ119760 possessions, and he gaveВҰ119761 the changesВҰ119762 of clothes for the riddleВҰ119764. \add вүҲButВҰ119746 he was very angry, so\add* he went \add вүҲback to his parent's home\add*.
\v 20 Then \add (unknown to ShimshonВҰ119774)\add*, \add *his\add* wifeВҰ119773 \add вүҲwas given to the man who'd been\add* his closeВҰ119775 friendВҰ119777 andВҰ119772 companionВҰ119775.
\c 15
\rem /s1 Samson's Vengeance on the Philistines; Samson Defeats the Philistines
\p
\v 1 Some daysВҰ119781 later during the wheatВҰ119785 harvestВҰ119783, ShimshonВҰ119787 visitedВҰ119786 his wife with a youngВҰ119791 goatВҰ119791 \add as a present for the family, because\add* he said, вҖңI'll go into the bedroom with my wife.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ119780\add* herВҰ119802 fatherВҰ119802 wouldn't allow him to go inВҰ119782,
\v 2 andВҰ119805 \add вүҲpleaded\add*, вҖңTruly, I \add вүҲI thoughtВҰ119808 that you must\add* hateВҰ119811 her, so I gaveВҰ119813 her to your closeВҰ119814 friendВҰ119814. \add вүҲButВҰ119805 wouldn't\add* her youngerВҰ119817 sisterВҰ119816 be better \add anyway\add*? Please, \add вүҲwould you take her insteadВҰ119824\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 ShimshonВҰ119828 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ119826\add*, вҖңThis timeВҰ119830 I'm blameless concerning the PhilistinesВҰ119831 when I \add вүҲcause trouble for\add* them.вҖқ
\v 4 ThenВҰ119839 \add *he\add* wentВҰ119839 and capturedВҰ119841 threeВҰ119842 hundredВҰ119844 foxesВҰ119845 and \add вүҲtied them inВҰ119860 pairs\add*вҖ”tail to tail. HeВҰ119840 tookВҰ119846 torches, and \add вүҲtied\add* one torch betweenВҰ119856 \add вүҲthe tailsВҰ119859 of each pair\add*.
\v 5 He \add вүҲlit\add* the torchesВҰ119865 and let \add @the foxes\add* loose into the grain \add вүҲcrops\add* of the PhilistinesВҰ119868. As a result, he burntВҰ119869 both the standing grain \add plants\add* and also the \add harvested\add* \add #stacks\add* of sheavesВҰ119870, and even a vineyardВҰ119876 and an oliveВҰ119877 orchard.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ119879\add* the PhilistinesВҰ119880 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWho did this?вҖқ
