\v 17 WhenВҰ120092 he finishedВҰ120093 \add вүҲreciting that\add*, he hurled the jawbone \add вүҲaway\add*, andВҰ120092 he calledВҰ120098 that placeВҰ120099 вҖҳRamatВҰ120101-LehiВҰ120102вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳjawbone hillвҖҷ)\add*.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ120104 he was very thirsty and cried out to YahwehВҰ120109, вҖңYou yourself have givenВҰ120112 your servantВҰ120115 this great victoryВҰ120118, \add вүҲbutВҰ120104\add* now mustВҰ120122 I dieВҰ120122 withВҰ120113 this thirst and \add вүҲget captured by those\add* uncircumcisedВҰ120126 \add Philistines\add*?вҖқ
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ120128\add* GodВҰ120129 splitВҰ120128 open the \add little\add* hollowВҰ120132 that's atВҰ120135 Lehi, and waterВҰ120138 came out of it. WhenВҰ120128 he drankВҰ120139, his \add вүҲstrength\add* returnedВҰ120140 and he revivedВҰ120142. Because of that, he called it вҖҳEyn-HakkoreВҰ120150вҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳthe fountain of the one who called outвҖҷ)\add*, which is inВҰ120135 Lehi to this dayВҰ120154.
\v 20 And \add so\add* \add @Shimshon\add* led YisraelВҰ120160 for twentyВҰ120163 years atВҰ120161 the timeВҰ120161 of the Philistine \add oppression\add*.
\c 16
