\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ120460 she saidВҰ120460 to him, вҖңHow can you sayВҰ120463, вҖҳI loveВҰ120464 you,вҖҷ when your heartВҰ120465 isn'tВҰ120466 withВҰ120472 me? You've \add вүҲbeen deceitfulВҰ120471 to\add* me threeВҰ120469 timesВҰ120470 \add now\add*, andВҰ120460 you haven't revealed to me \add вүҲthe secret of your amazing\add* strengthВҰ120478.вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲDay after day she nagged andВҰ120481 pesteredВҰ120490 him until he was sick to deathВҰ120493 of hearing it\add*.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ120495\add* \add finally\add* he told her \add вүҲhis secret\add*, вҖң\add вүҲMy hair has never been cut\add* because I've been a NaziriteВҰ120514 to GodВҰ120515 \add вүҲsince my birth\add*. If \add вүҲmy headВҰ120511\add* would be shavedВҰ120521, thenВҰ120495 my strengthВҰ120524 would leaveВҰ120522 me, andВҰ120495 I'd becomeВҰ120525 weakвҖ”I'd be just like any other \add #man\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 WhenВҰ120531 DelilahВҰ120532 perceived that he'd told her \add вүҲhis deepest secret\add*, sheВҰ120544 summoned the Philistine leaders, вҖңCome \add вүҲhere\add* one more timeВҰ120550, because he's told me \add вүҲhis secret\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ120531\add* the Philistine leaders cameВҰ120561, bringing the silverВҰ120566 \add coins\add* \add вүҲwithВҰ120567 them\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ120576 she made him fall asleepВҰ120569 on herВҰ120572 kneesВҰ120572, and she calledВҰ120573 in a manВҰ120574 to shaveВҰ120575 off his sevenВҰ120578 locks \add вүҲof hair\add*, causing him to start to weaken, and his \add additional\add* strengthВҰ120584 left him.
\v 20 ThenВҰ120587 she said, вҖңThe PhilistinesВҰ120588 are \add вүҲhere to get\add* you, ShimshonВҰ120590!вҖқ He woke up and \add вүҲthought to himself\add*, вҖңI'll escape like \add вүҲall the other times\add* and I'll shakeВҰ120597 myselfВҰ120597 loose.вҖқ ButВҰ120587 he didn'tВҰ120599 know that YahwehВҰ120602 had left him.
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ120606\add* the PhilistinesВҰ120607 seizedВҰ120606 him, and they gougedВҰ120608 out his eyesВҰ120611. They broughtВҰ120612 him to GazaВҰ120614 and chained him withВҰ120616 a pair of bronzeВҰ120616 shacklesВҰ120616, thenВҰ120606 \add вүҲthey put him to work inВҰ120616 prisonВҰ120620\add* grindingВҰ120618 \add grain\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add over time\add* his hairВҰ120624 beganВҰ120623 to grow back again.
\s1 Shimshon's death
