\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ120902 after the money had been returnedВҰ120902,\add* his mother gave two hundredВҰ120909 silver coins to a silversmith. He made a carvedВҰ120914 figure and one cast \add from a mould\add*, and \add they were placed\add* in Micah's houseВҰ120917.
\p
\v 5 NowВҰ120929 that MicahВҰ120921 had a \add вүҲshrine with gods in it\add*, he made \add вүҲsome priestly robes\add* and \add вүҲsome householdВҰ120923 gods\add*, and consecrated one of his sonsВҰ120933 as his priestВҰ120937.
\v 6 In thoseВҰ120940 daysВҰ120939, YisraelВҰ120943 didn'tВҰ120941 have a kingВҰ120942вҖ”each \add вүҲperson\add* would do whatever \add вүҲseemed rightВҰ120945 to them\add*.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲNow\add* thereВҰ120963 was a youngВҰ120952 LeviteВҰ120959 manВҰ120952 from the family of Yehudah\f + \fr 17:7 \ft Maybe one parent was from the tribe of Levi and one from Yehudah?\f* who'd been staying in Bethlehem (in Yehudah).
\v 8 \add *He\add* left Bethlehem to find another place to say, andВҰ120965 onВҰ120972 his way, he \add вүҲended up arriving\add* atВҰ120972 Micah'sВҰ120981 place inВҰ120972 the Efrayimite hill countryВҰ120975.
\v 9 вҖңWhere have youВҰ120990 comeВҰ120990 from?вҖқ MicahВҰ120988 \add вүҲasked\add* him.
\p вҖңI'm a LeviteВҰ120993 from Bethlehem inВҰ121001 YehudahВҰ120997,вҖқ he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңandВҰ120985 I'm \add вүҲtrying to find a good place to stayВҰ121000 a while\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңStayВҰ121014 with me,вҖқ saidВҰ121004 MicahВҰ121006, вҖңand be like a fatherВҰ121012 and a priestВҰ121013 to me. I'llВҰ121015 giveВҰ121015 you tenВҰ121018 silverВҰ121019 coins a yearВҰ121020 as well as \add вүҲboard and clothing\add*.вҖқ SoВҰ121004 the LeviteВҰ121025 \add man\add* wentВҰ121024 in
\v 11 andВҰ121033 agreedВҰ121027 to stayВҰ121029 with \add @Micah\add*, \add eventually\add* becoming like one of Micah'sВҰ121028 \add own\add* sonsВҰ121037.
\v 12 MicahВҰ121040 ordained the LeviteВҰ121044, and the youngВҰ121048 manВҰ121048 became like a priestВҰ121049 to him, and lived in \add *his\add* houseВҰ121051.
\v 13 вҖңNow I knowВҰ121057 that YahwehВҰ121061 will \add вүҲmake everything go well\add* for me,вҖқ MicahВҰ121055 saidВҰ121054, вҖңbecause I have this LeviteВҰ121067 as a priestВҰ121068.вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 The Danites settle in Layish
\rem /s1 The Danites settle in Layish; Micah and the Tribe of Dan; Idolatry in the Tribe of Dan; The Migration of Dan
\p
\v 1 In those days, YisraelВҰ121074 \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ121072 have a\add* king. The tribe of Dan was lookingВҰ121079 forВҰ121079 land to settle inВҰ121074, because up \add вүҲuntilВҰ121089 then\add*, \add вүҲthey hadn't been able to claim their allocated region\add* among the IsraeliВҰ121095 tribes.
\v 2 \add вүҲSo\add* the Danites sent out five capable men (from ZorahВҰ121113 and from EshtaolВҰ121114) to scout out the region and explore it. They had told them, вҖңGo \add and\add* explore the area.вҖқ They came to the Efrayimite hill countryВҰ121128, as far as Micah'sВҰ121134 houseВҰ121133, and spentВҰ121135 the nightВҰ121135 thereВҰ121136.
\v 3 They'd been near Micah'sВҰ121142 houseВҰ121141 \add вүҲwhen\add* they recognizedВҰ121144 the voiceВҰ121147 of the youngВҰ121148 LeviteВҰ121149 manВҰ121148. So they'd \add вүҲgone in\add* thereВҰ121151 and they \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWho broughtВҰ121156 you here? What are you doingВҰ121161 in this \add placeВҰ121162\add*? What do you \add вүҲget\add* here?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ121168 he told them what MicahВҰ121174 had done for him, andВҰ121168 how he'd hiredВҰ121175 him to be like his priestВҰ121179.
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ121181\add* theyВҰ121181 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңPlease find out from GodВҰ121186 if we'll have successВҰ121188 on this expedition we're on.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 вҖң\add вүҲContinue onВҰ121206\add* inВҰ121206 peaceВҰ121199,вҖқ the priestВҰ121197 saidВҰ121195. вҖңYahwehВҰ121201 has \add вүҲprepared everything ahead\add* of you all.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 Then the fiveВҰ121210 menВҰ121211 left and \add вүҲwentВҰ121212 onВҰ121220\add* to LayishВҰ121213. They sawВҰ121214 thatВҰ121218 the peopleВҰ121217 \add вүҲthere\add* were livingВҰ121221 in confidence \add вүҲjust like\add* the Tsidonians wereвҖ”\add вүҲpeacefullyВҰ121226\add* and \add feeling\add* secureВҰ121223. No one in the region was causing \add вүҲtrouble\add* for them and \add вүҲthey were very settled\add*. They were far away from the Tsidonians and \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ121240 interact withВҰ121220 others\add*.
\v 8 ThenВҰ121247 they wentВҰ121247 \add back\add* to their relatives in TsorahВҰ121251 andВҰ121247 EshtaolВҰ121252, who \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңHow \add вүҲdid it go\add*?вҖқ
\v 9 вҖңGet \add вүҲready immediately\add*,вҖқ they \add вүҲsaid\add*, вҖңso that we can go \add to battle\add* againstВҰ121262 them! Because we've seen the land andВҰ121259 listen, it's incredible good. \add вүҲDon't just still there\add*вҖ”you all \add вүҲneed to take action\add* to go in to \add вүҲtake possessionВҰ121278 of\add* the land.
\p
\v 10 When you goВҰ121283, you'll all comeВҰ121284 to a peopleВҰ121288 living \add вүҲwithout suspicion of attack\add*, andВҰ121290 the land is spacious inВҰ121297 \add вүҲall directions\add*, because GodВҰ121296 \add вүҲwill handВҰ121297 itВҰ121295 over to you\add*вҖ”a placeВҰ121298 whereВҰ121299 there's no lack of anything that's onВҰ121297 the earth.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 SoВҰ121310 sixВҰ121316 hundredВҰ121318 DaniteВҰ121313 \add вүҲwarriors\add* leftВҰ121310 TsorahВҰ121314 andВҰ121315 EshtaolВҰ121315, carrying their weaponsВҰ121321.
\v 12 They \add вүҲset off\add* andВҰ121325 camped atВҰ121326 Kiriat-Yearim inВҰ121326 YehudahВҰ121328. \add вүҲThat's why\add* theyВҰ121332 call that placeВҰ121333 MahanehВҰ121335-Dan \add (meaning вҖҳDan'sВҰ121337 campвҖҷ)\add* to this dayВҰ121339вҖ”it's back behindВҰ121342 Kiriat-Yearim.
\v 13 From thereВҰ121347, theyВҰ121351 crossed over into the Efrayimite hill countryВҰ121348, \add eventually\add* \add вүҲarriving near\add* Micah'sВҰ121355 houseВҰ121354.
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ121357 the fiveВҰ121358 menВҰ121359 who had \add вүҲbeen here previously\add* scouting out the land saidВҰ121366 to theirВҰ121369 \add вүҲgroup\add*, вҖңDoВҰ121365 you knowВҰ121370 that there'sВҰ121372 \add вүҲa houseВҰ121373 here\add* withВҰ121373 a \add вүҲgear for priests\add*, family idols, a carvedВҰ121377 image, andВҰ121357 a cast image? SoВҰ121357 now, considerВҰ121380 what you should do.вҖқ
\v 15 SoВҰ121385 they turnedВҰ121385 \add вүҲoff the main path\add* and they came to the place with the youngВҰ121392 LeviteВҰ121393 man in Micah'sВҰ121395 house, and they askedВҰ121396 about his welfareВҰ121399.
\v 16 The sixВҰ121401 hundredВҰ121403 Danite men stayed outside at the gateВҰ121410, holding theirВҰ121407 weaponsВҰ121406.
\p
\v 17 The five men who'd gone to scout out the land went in \add around the back\add*. They took the carvedВҰ121429 image, the priest's gear, the family idols, andВҰ121416 the cast image, while the priest was standingВҰ121440 at the entranceВҰ121441 of the gateВҰ121442 along with the six hundredВҰ121445 armedВҰ121447 men.
\v 18 WhenВҰ121451 the priestВҰ121468 saw them bringing out \add вүҲall the religious objects\add*, he \add вүҲdemanded\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWhat'sВҰ121454 going on\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңStay quietВҰ121475,вҖқ they told him. вҖңPut your handВҰ121478 over your mouthВҰ121481 and come withВҰ121501 us, and be like a fatherВҰ121487 and a priest for us. Is it betterВҰ121489 to be a priest for \add only\add* \add вүҲone householdВҰ121493\add*, or to be a priest for a \add whole\add* related tribeВҰ121499 inВҰ121501 YisraelВҰ121501?вҖқ
\v 20 The priest \add вүҲliked that idea\add*, so he wentВҰ121516 along withВҰ121517 themвҖ”taking the \add вүҲpriestly gear\add* and the \add вүҲhousehold idols\add*, and the carvedВҰ121515 imageВҰ121515.
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ121520 they \add wentВҰ121521 back to the main path\add* and continued on theirВҰ121532 way with the children, animals, and \add those carrying\add* the valuableВҰ121531 property going in frontВҰ121532.
\v 22 When they'd already gone \add вүҲquite some\add* distance from Micah'sВҰ121537 houseВҰ121540, Micah and \add вүҲhis neighbours\add* gathered togetherВҰ121546, then the menВҰ121538 ran \add inВҰ121540 a group\add* and caught up withВҰ121540 the \add вүҲDanites\add*.
\v 23 They calledВҰ121568 \add вүҲout to the Danites\add* who turnedВҰ121560 around \add вүҲto faceВҰ121561 them\add* andВҰ121554 \add вүҲasked\add* MicahВҰ121563, вҖңWhat's \add вүҲthe matter? Why has this group come\add* togetherВҰ121568?вҖқ
\v 24 вҖңYou all took my godsВҰ121573 thatВҰ121574 I made,вҖқ Micah \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңAnd the priestВҰ121580. ThenВҰ121570 you \add вүҲdisappeared andВҰ121570 I had nothing left\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ121570\add* how can you all \add вүҲask\add* me what \add вүҲthe matter is\add*!вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖң\add вүҲI wouldn't say too much if I was you,вҖқ he was told. вҖңOtherwise some of our more fiery menВҰ121609 might start to get a bit hostile, thenВҰ121595 you'd bring about your own death, andВҰ121595 that of your companions\add*!вҖқ
\v 26 ThenВҰ121617 MicahВҰ121623 realisedВҰ121622 that they were too strongВҰ121626 for \add #them\add*, so \add #they\add* turnedВҰ121629 back around andВҰ121617 wentВҰ121617 homeВҰ121633.
\rem /s1 The Danites Settle in Layish
\p \add вүҲSoВҰ121617\add* the DanitesВҰ121620 continued onward,
\v 27 taking with them the things thatВҰ121638 MicahВҰ121641 had made, as well as his priestВҰ121644. They cameВҰ121649 to LayishВҰ121652 where the unsuspectingВҰ121657 peopleВҰ121655 were living peaceablyВҰ121656, and they slaughtered them with their swordsВҰ121662 and burntВҰ121666 down the cityВҰ121665.
\v 28 \add вүҲNo one came to rescue them\add* because it was \add вүҲa long way\add* from Tsidon and \add вүҲthey did have much involvement withВҰ121684 them anyway\add*. (\add @Layish\add* was inВҰ121684 the valleyВҰ121684 near Beyt-Rehob.) They rebuiltВҰ121689 the cityВҰ121692 and thenВҰ121669 \add вүҲmoved into\add* it.
\v 29 They named the \add rebuilt\add* city Dan (instead of LayishВҰ121708) in honour of theirВҰ121703 ancestorВҰ121703 Dan who was one of Yisrael'sВҰ121706 sons.
\v 30 The Danites \add вүҲmounted\add* the carvedВҰ121721 imageВҰ121721 for themselves \add to worship\add*. Yonatan (Gershom'sВҰ121725 son from Menashsheh) became the priest for the Danites (andВҰ121714 thenВҰ121714 his descendantsВҰ121716 untilВҰ121736 when the people were \add eventually\add* exiled from the region).
\v 31 \add вүҲSoВҰ121742\add* theyВҰ121742 set up the carvedВҰ121746 imageВҰ121746 that MicahВҰ121747 had made \add andВҰ121742 worshipped it\add* \add вүҲthe whole timeВҰ121752 that God'sВҰ121744 tent\add* was at ShilohВҰ121757.
\c 19
\s1 The Levite and his slave-wife
\rem /s1 The Levite and His Concubine; A Levite and His Concubine; The Levite's Concubine
\p
\v 1 In thoseВҰ121762 daysВҰ121761 when there was no kingВҰ121763 over YisraelВҰ121765, there was a LeviteВҰ121769 man who was staying in the remotestВҰ121771 partsВҰ121771 of the hill countryВҰ121772 of EfrayimВҰ121774. He took a slave-wife for himself from Bethlehem in YehudahВҰ121782.
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever\add*, \add *she\add* started sleeping around, and thenВҰ121784 she left himВҰ121788 and wentВҰ121787 to herВҰ121792 father'sВҰ121792 houseВҰ121791 in Bethlehem \add where she ended up\add* staying for fourВҰ121802 monthsВҰ121803.
\v 3 ThenВҰ121805 her husband \add вүҲgot organised\add* and wentВҰ121807 afterВҰ121808 herвҖ”to \add вүҲsweet-talk\add* her and persuade her to return with him. He took a youngВҰ121824 \add servantВҰ121815\add* man and a team of donkeysВҰ121818. She invited \add @her husband\add* into her father's houseВҰ121820, and when \add *her\add* father sawВҰ121822 him, he was glad to meet him.
\v 4 His father-in-law (her father) insisted \add вүҲon offering hospitality\add*, so they ateВҰ121838 and drankВҰ121839, and he stayed the nightВҰ121840, and \add ended up\add* staying for threeВҰ121836 daysВҰ121837.
\v 5 ThenВҰ121843 onВҰ121847 the fourthВҰ121845 dayВҰ121844, they got up earlyВҰ121846 andВҰ121843 \add @the Levite\add* prepared to leave, butВҰ121843 his father-in-law \add вүҲurged him to eat before they left\add*.
