\v 9 \add вүҲWhenВҰ121914\add* the man stood up to go with his slave-wife and his youngВҰ121924 man, his father-in-law said, вҖңListen, the day's \add вүҲcoming to an end soon\add*. Please stay the night. See, \add вүҲit'll be getting dark soon\add*. Spend the night here and \add вүҲbe happy\add*. ThenВҰ121914 make an earlyВҰ121940 start tomorrowВҰ121941 for your journeyВҰ121942 \add вүҲhomeВҰ121944\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ121946\add* the manВҰ121949 from the tribe of Levi didn'tВҰ121946 want to stay another nightВҰ121950. He put saddlesВҰ121963 on his two donkeysВҰ121962, and started to go with his slave-wife and his servant toward YebusВҰ121957 city (now called YerushalemВҰ121959).
