\v 11 They got close to YebusВҰ121987 and the daylight had \add вүҲmostly gone, so\add* the young man saidВҰ121974 to his masterВҰ121978, вҖңCome, pleaseВҰ121981, we shouldВҰ121982 turnВҰ121982 asideВҰ121982 into this cityВҰ121985 of the Yebusites so we can spendВҰ121989 the nightВҰ121989 there.вҖқ
\v 12 вҖңWe won'tВҰ121995 \add вүҲgoВҰ122007\add* into a into a cityВҰ121999 of \add #foreigners\add*, his masterВҰ121994 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңThere's no \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122005 there\add*. \add вүҲBetter to keep going until weВҰ121996\add* reach GibeahВҰ122010.вҖқ
\v 13 ThenВҰ122012 he \add вүҲadded\add*, вҖң\add вүҲYes, let's keep going to reachВҰ122017\add* either GibeahВҰ122021 or RamahВҰ122023 to spendВҰ122020 the nightВҰ122020 inВҰ122018.вҖқ
\v 14 SoВҰ122025 they passedВҰ122025 \add Yebus\add* andВҰ122025 went on, \add вүҲbutВҰ122025\add* the sunВҰ122029 went down as they neared GibeahВҰ122031 (in Benyamite \add territory\add*)
\v 15 \add вүҲso\add* they went into GibeahВҰ122039 to spend the night thereВҰ122036. TheyВҰ122048 went andВҰ122035 sat inВҰ122039 the open plaza of the cityВҰ122043, \add вүҲbutВҰ122035\add* no one \add вүҲinvited them into their homeВҰ122049 for the night\add*.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲButВҰ122052\add* thenВҰ122052 in \add late\add* eveningВҰ122063, an old man came in from his work in the fieldВҰ122062. \add *He\add* was from the Efrayimite hill country \add вүҲbutВҰ122052\add* \add currently\add* staying in the GibeahВҰ122070 area \add вүҲwhere\add* the \add вүҲresidents\add* were Benyamites.
\v 17 He \add вүҲlooked up\add* and \add вүҲnoticedВҰ122078 them\add* inВҰ122083 the open plaza of the cityВҰ122084 and \add вүҲasked\add* the man, вҖңWhere are you goingВҰ122091, and where have you come from?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖңWe're passingВҰ122097 through from Bethlehem in YehudahВҰ122116,вҖқ \add @the Levite\add* \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңGoing to the remoteВҰ122105 partsВҰ122105 of the Efrayimite hill countryВҰ122106 \add вүҲwhere I'm from\add*. I went to Bethlehem, andВҰ122095 I'm goingВҰ122122 to \add Shiloh where\add* Yahweh's house is. \add вүҲHowever,\add* no one \add вүҲhere has invited us into their home\add*.
\v 19 \add We have our own\add* food and strawВҰ122131 for our donkeysВҰ122136, and \add enough\add* food and wine for \add вүҲthe three of us\add* \add so\add* we don'tВҰ122148 need anything else.
\p
\v 20 вҖңPeace to you all,вҖқ saidВҰ122154 the old manВҰ122155. вҖң\add вүҲLet me supply\add* everything you needвҖ”only don'tВҰ122166 spendВҰ122168 the nightВҰ122168 \add here\add* inВҰ122165 the squareВҰ122165.вҖқ
\v 21 ThenВҰ122170 he took \add #them\add* to his houseВҰ122171 and fed \add &their\add* donkeysВҰ122176. TheyВҰ122176 washedВҰ122177 their feetВҰ122178, and they \add all\add* ateВҰ122179 and drankВҰ122180.
\rem /s1 Gibeah's Crime
\v 22 They were \add вүҲhaving a good time\add*, butВҰ122187 suddenly the men of the cityВҰ122189вҖ”wicked menвҖ”had \add вүҲsurroundedВҰ122194\add* the houseвҖ”pounding repeatedly on the doorВҰ122201. They \add вүҲcalled out\add* to the old man \add вүҲwho owned\add* the house, вҖң\add Hey,\add* bringВҰ122210 out the man who came to your \add вүҲplace\add*, so we \add вүҲcan have fun with\add* him.вҖқ\f + \fr 19:22 \ft Of course, everyone understood that their aim was to sodomise him.\f*\x + \xo 19:22-24: \xt Gen 19:5-8.\x*
\v 23 The man \add вүҲwho owned\add* the house went out to them andВҰ122222 said to them, вҖңNo, my brothersВҰ122231, pleaseВҰ122235 you mustn't act wickedly. \add вүҲThat man is a guest in\add* my houseвҖ”you all mustn't do this disgracefulВҰ122251 thingВҰ122251.
\v 24 My virginВҰ122256 daughterВҰ122255 and his slave-wife are here. Please let me bringВҰ122258 \em them\em* out so you can ravishВҰ122262 them and do \add вүҲwhatever you want\add* to them. ButВҰ122257 don'tВҰ122270 do that wicked thingВҰ122272 to that manВҰ122268.вҖқ
\v 25 ButВҰ122289 the menВҰ122279 weren't willingВҰ122278 to listenВҰ122280 to him, so the manВҰ122283 \add вүҲpushed his slave-wife out\add* to them and they \add вүҲraped\add* her and abusedВҰ122290 her the whole nightВҰ122295 untilВҰ122296 the morningВҰ122298, \add вүҲwhen\add* they \add вүҲdiscarded\add* her \add вүҲas it began to\add* dawn.
\p
\v 26 The womanВҰ122305 \add вүҲmanaged to get herself back to\add* the houseВҰ122310 whereВҰ122313 herВҰ122315 masterВҰ122315 was, andВҰ122308 \add вүҲcollapsed\add* at the entranceВҰ122309 untilВҰ122317 \add вүҲit got lightВҰ122319\add*.
\v 27 \add вүҲWhenВҰ122321\add* her masterВҰ122322 got up and he openedВҰ122324 the door to goВҰ122328 \add вүҲand continue on his trip\add*, look, his slave-wife had fallen atВҰ122323 the entranceВҰ122334 and her handsВҰ122336 were on the thresholdВҰ122339.
\v 28 вҖңGet up,вҖқ he told her. вҖңLet's goВҰ122344.вҖқ ButВҰ122341 she didn'tВҰ122345 answerВҰ122346, so he put her on his donkeyВҰ122350 andВҰ122341 \add вүҲheaded\add* homeВҰ122354.
\v 29 WhenВҰ122356 he \add вүҲarrived\add*, he got a knifeВҰ122363 and hacked his wife's \add body\add* into twelve piecesВҰ122370 (\add вүҲincludingВҰ122360 the\add* bonesВҰ122367), and he sentВҰ122371 \add #them\add* \add вүҲto various places spread across\add* all of Yisrael'sВҰ122374 territoryВҰ122373.
\v 30 ThenВҰ122376 everyoneВҰ122377 who sawВҰ122379 \add @a piece\add* said, вҖңNothing has \add ever\add* happened like this beforeвҖ”we've never seenВҰ122386 anything like this from the time that the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122392\add* left EgyptВҰ122394 untilВҰ122395 \add вүҲnow\add*. \add вүҲWhat do we need to do about it?\add* Speak up andВҰ122376 make a plan.вҖқ
\c 20
\s1 The preparation of Israelis of war
\rem /s1 Israelites Fight the Benjamites; The Other Tribes Attack Benjamin; Israel Prepares for War; Israel's War with Benjamin; The Benjamites
\p
\v 1 Then all the IsraelisВҰ122410 from DanВҰ122415 \add in the north\add* to BeerВҰ122418-Sheva \add in the south\add*, and \add even\add* from GileadВҰ122421 \add across the Yordan\add*, came and assembledВҰ122411 before YahwehВҰ122424 at Mitspah with \add вүҲone single, united purpose\add*.
\v 2 TheВҰ122434 leaders of all the IsraeliВҰ122433 tribesВҰ122433 \add вүҲalso came out to show their agreement withВҰ122435\add* the assemblyВҰ122435 of the people of the true GodВҰ122437: four hundredВҰ122439 thousandВҰ122440 warriors all carrying swordsВҰ122444.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the \add вүҲBenyamites\add* had heardВҰ122447 that the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122455\add* had gathered at Mitspah, and \add вүҲeveryoneВҰ122453 asked\add*, вҖңExplain how this wicked thing \add вүҲcame to happen\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ122466\add* the LeviteВҰ122468 man (the husbandВҰ122469 of the womanВҰ122470 who had been murderedВҰ122471) answeredВҰ122466, вҖңI wentВҰ122476 to the GibeahВҰ122473 \add region\add* (in BenyaminВҰ122475) with my slave-wife to spendВҰ122479 the nightВҰ122479.
\v 5 The citizensВҰ122483 of GibeahВҰ122484 \add вүҲconspired\add* \add together\add* againstВҰ122482 me. They surroundedВҰ122485 the houseВҰ122489 at nightВҰ122490 becauseВҰ122486 of me, intendingВҰ122492 to killВҰ122493 me. Instead, they assaulted \add andВҰ122481 abusedВҰ122497\add* myВҰ122486 slave-wife \add вүҲso that\add* sheВҰ122498 diedВҰ122498.
\v 6 I tookВҰ122500 my slave-wife's \add body\add* back \add home\add* and cut her inВҰ122501 piecesВҰ122502, and I sentВҰ122503 \add #them\add* out into every \add вүҲsection of the territory that God gave\add* Yisrael, because they've committed a heinous crime, and a disgraceВҰ122512 to Yisrael.
\v 7 Listen, all of youВҰ122516 IsraelisВҰ122518, \add вүҲwhat's yourВҰ122516 advice? What should we do about it?\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 All the peopleВҰ122528 \add вүҲagreed together andВҰ122536\add* started saying, вҖңWe won't goВҰ122533 back to our \add вүҲfamilies\add*. We won't return to our housesВҰ122539.
\v 9 \add вүҲrather\add* this is what weВҰ122545 mustВҰ122545 do to GibeahВҰ122546: \add вүҲchoose by lot who will fight against\add* \add #them\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲChooseВҰ122574 a tenth of our menВҰ122552\add* to \add go andВҰ122550\add* get supplies \add for the other warriorsВҰ122552 to travel\add* to GibeahВҰ122567 inВҰ122574 BenyaminВҰ122568 \add after what theyВҰ122566 did thatВҰ122572\add* outragedВҰ122571 YisraelВҰ122557.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ122576\add* all YisraelВҰ122580 was unitedВҰ122586 together against that cityВҰ122583.
\p
\v 12 Then the IsraeliВҰ122591 tribes sentВҰ122589 menВҰ122592 \add вүҲacross the Benyamite region to ask\add*, вҖңWhat's this \add вүҲevilВҰ122599 thing\add* that's been done amongВҰ122603 youВҰ122603?
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ122605\add* now, hand over those worthlessВҰ122612 menВҰ122609 from the GibeahВҰ122614 \add region\add* so that we can put them to deathВҰ122615 andВҰ122605 purgeВҰ122616 YisraelВҰ122618 of that evilВҰ122617.вҖқ ButВҰ122605 the Benyamites weren't willingВҰ122620 to \add вүҲtake the advice of theirВҰ122626 IsraeliВҰ122627 relatives\add*.
\v 14 \add *They\add* cameВҰ122631 out of their citiesВҰ122637 \add andВҰ122631 assembled\add* at GibeahВҰ122638 to the battleВҰ122640 against the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122644\add*.
\v 15 The \add вүҲBenyamites \add* mobilised together twenty-six thousandВҰ122654 men from their citiesВҰ122651 on that dayВҰ122649, all carrying \add #swords\add*. In addition, sevenВҰ122662 hundredВҰ122663 chosenВҰ122665 men had been mobilised from the GibeahВҰ122660 \add region\add*.
\v 16 Among all of those peopleВҰ122669 were sevenВҰ122671 hundredВҰ122672 chosenВҰ122674 left-handers, each of whom could slingВҰ122682 a stoneВҰ122683 atВҰ122683 a hairВҰ122686 without missing.
\v 17 The IsraelisВҰ122692 (excluding Benyamites) musteredВҰ122693 up for themselves fourВҰ122696 hundredВҰ122697 thousandВҰ122698 menВҰ122691вҖ”all \add вүҲexpert warriorsВҰ122691\add* and all carrying \add #swords\add*.
\s1 The war to punish the Benyamites
\rem /s1 The War against the Benjaminites
\p
\v 18 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122717\add* got ready and wentВҰ122709 to Beyt-El and asked GodВҰ122714, вҖңWho should \add вүҲlead us into\add* battleВҰ122723 withВҰ122714 the \add вүҲBenyamites\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңIt should be YehudahВҰ122730 \add вүҲout front,\add*вҖқ YahwehВҰ122729 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ122715\add*.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲSoВҰ122733\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122736 set out\add* inВҰ122737 the morningВҰ122737 andВҰ122738 made camp near GibeahВҰ122741.
\v 20 Then \add *they\add* wentВҰ122744 out to battle against the BenyamitesвҖ”setting themselves up for the battle against them at GibeahВҰ122759.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲButВҰ122761 the Benyamites led a surprise attack\add* out of GibeahВҰ122767 andВҰ122761 killed twenty-two thousandВҰ122774 of the \add вүҲIsraeli warriors\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲHowever the IsraelisВҰ122781\add* strengthened themselves andВҰ122782 theyВҰ122788 continued to set up for battleВҰ122784 \add вүҲthe next\add* dayВҰ122790 atВҰ122785 the \add вүҲsame\add* placeВҰ122785.
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ122793 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122796 assembled\add* and wept before Yahweh untilВҰ122801 eveningВҰ122803. They asked \add *him\add*, вҖңShould \add #we\add* continue to attack and battleВҰ122809 against \add #our\add* \add вүҲcousins the Benyamites\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲback\add* against \add #them\add*,вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲSo the IsraelisВҰ122824 went back to battle against the Benyamites\add* \add again\add* on the secondВҰ122830 dayВҰ122829.
\v 25 \add Again\add* the Benyamites came out from GibeahВҰ122839, andВҰ122832 \add this time\add* theyВҰ122842 killed eighteenВҰ122846 thousandВҰ122848 \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ122843 swordsmenВҰ122855\add*.
\v 26 ThenВҰ122857 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ122860 warriors\add* and all the peopleВҰ122860 wentВҰ122857 \add вүҲback\add* to Beyt-El. They wept, and they sat thereВҰ122871 before Yahweh. They fastedВҰ122874 that dayВҰ122875 untilВҰ122878 the eveningВҰ122880, thenВҰ122857 they offered burntВҰ122882 offerings and peaceВҰ122883 offerings to Yahweh.
\v 27 \add *They\add* asked YahwehВҰ122891 (because the boxВҰ122893 containing the agreement withВҰ122891 the true GodВҰ122895 was thereВҰ122892 inВҰ122891 thoseВҰ122897 daysВҰ122896
\v 28 andВҰ122899 Finehas (son of Aharon's son EleazarВҰ122902) was serving beforeВҰ122908 it inВҰ122931 thoseВҰ122910 daysВҰ122909), вҖңShould \add #we\add* continue to go to the battleВҰ122915 once more against the our \add вүҲcousins the Benyamites\add*, or should \add #we\add* stop?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add вүҲback\add* \add again\add*, because tomorrowВҰ122929 I'llВҰ122930 giveВҰ122930 \add вүҲyou victory over them\add*,вҖқ YahwehВҰ122926 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ122925\add*.
\p
\v 29 \add вүҲSoВҰ122933 the IsraelisВҰ122934\add* placed \add вүҲgroups of warriors in ambushВҰ122935\add* \add all\add* around GibeahВҰ122938.
\v 30 Then \add *they\add* \add вүҲtookВҰ122952 their positionsВҰ122952\add* \add now\add* for the thirdВҰ122951 dayВҰ122950 against the Benyamites inВҰ122957 GibeahВҰ122955.
\v 31 \add вүҲWhenВҰ122959 the Benyamites\add* came out from the cityВҰ122968, they were lured away as they beganВҰ122969 to strikeВҰ122970 down their enemies like the time before. Around thirtyВҰ122986 \add вүҲIsraelis\add* were killed onВҰ122975 the \add two\add* roadsвҖ”one goingВҰ122979 to Beyt-El andВҰ122959 the otherВҰ122983 to GibeahВҰ122984 through the countrysideВҰ122985.
\v 32 ThenВҰ122990 the \add вүҲBenyamites\add* said, вҖң\add вүҲWe're starting to defeatВҰ122993 them\add*, just \add вүҲlike beforeВҰ122995\add*.вҖқ
\p ButВҰ122990 the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ122998\add* had said, вҖңLet's flee so that we can draw \add #them\add* away from the cityВҰ123004 \add andВҰ122990\add* onto the roads.вҖқ
\v 33 ThenВҰ123009 \add the main group\add* of \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ123012 retreated\add* andВҰ123009 set up battle lines atВҰ123016 Baal-Tamar, \add вүҲas\add* the ones hiding in ambushВҰ123018 \add вүҲmade a surprise attack\add* from \add #their placesВҰ123014\add* in Maareh-Gibeah.
\v 34 Ten thousandВҰ123030 \add вүҲchosenВҰ123032 Israeli warriors\add* cameВҰ123026 out in the sight of the GibeahВҰ123028 region, andВҰ123026 the battleВҰ123036 was fierce, \add вүҲbutВҰ123026\add* \add @the Benyamites\add* hadn't yet realised that \add вүҲdisasterВҰ123045 was aboutВҰ123043 to hit them\add*.
\v 35 YahwehВҰ123049 \add helped the IsraelisВҰ123058 to defeatВҰ123048 the Benyamites\add* that dayВҰ123060, and \add вүҲover\add* twenty-five thousandВҰ123064 \add Benyamite\add* \add вүҲswordsmenВҰ123071 were killed\add*
\v 36 andВҰ123073 \add *they\add* sawВҰ123073 that they were defeatedВҰ123078.
\rem /s1 How the Israelites Won
\p The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ123082\add* had given ground to the \add вүҲBenyamites\add* because they had relied on the ambushВҰ123089 placedВҰ123083 around GibeahВҰ123094.
\v 37 ThenВҰ123096 the group hiding in ambush had rushedВҰ123098 out and spread out around GibeahВҰ123101, thenВҰ123096 had gone in and \add вүҲattacked the entireВҰ123107 cityВҰ123109 with their swordsВҰ123112\add*.
\v 38 ThenВҰ123117 theyВҰ123122 \add started a fire\add* as the \add вүҲprearranged signalВҰ123114\add* was to be the risingВҰ123123 column of smokeВҰ123124 up out of the cityВҰ123127.
\p
\v 39 Meanwhile the \add main\add* \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ123132 force\add* had retreated, and the Benyamites had attacked and killed around thirtyВҰ123141 menВҰ123138, thinking that they were winning like they'd done \add twice\add* beforeВҰ123149.
\v 40 \add вүҲButВҰ123153 when\add* the pillarВҰ123159 of smoke beganВҰ123154 to rise from the city, the \add вүҲBenyamitesВҰ123162\add* lookedВҰ123161 behindВҰ123163 them andВҰ123153 were shocked to see \add вүҲtheir city going up in smoke\add*.
\v 41 ThenВҰ123171 the \add main\add* \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ123171 force\add* \add stopped retreating andВҰ123174\add* turnedВҰ123173 back \add to attack again\add*. The \add вүҲBenyamites\add* were horrified because \add #they\add* \add now\add* sawВҰ123178 that disasterВҰ123183 had struck them.
\v 42 They retreatedВҰ123185 away from the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* into the wildernessВҰ123192, butВҰ123185 the battleВҰ123193 overtookВҰ123194 \add #them\add*, plusВҰ123193 \add @the Israelis\add* were coming \add back\add* out of the citiesВҰ123196 \add вүҲgetting right inВҰ123199 amongst them\add* \add to fight\add*.
\v 43 They surroundedВҰ123201 \add вүҲthe Benyamites as they tried to flee\add*, and easily ran \add #them\add* down as \add вүҲthey tried to escape from the GibeahВҰ123210 region towardsВҰ123211 the east\add*.
\v 44 Eighteen thousandВҰ123220 strong \add вүҲBenyamite warriorsВҰ123227 were killed\add*,
\v 45 and \add the rest\add* turnedВҰ123231 and fled into the wildernessВҰ123233 towardsВҰ123233 the RimmonВҰ123237 rockВҰ123236. \add вүҲAnother fiveВҰ123240 thousand men were killed\add* along the trails. They chased them \add вүҲall the way\add* to GidomВҰ123247, and killed \add another\add* twoВҰ123250 thousand men,
\v 46 \add вүҲso the totalВҰ123254 number of BenyamiteВҰ123257 swordsmenВҰ123263 who were killed came to\add* twenty-five thousandВҰ123260вҖ”all strong \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ123271\add*.
\p
\v 47 \add вүҲButВҰ123275\add* six hundredВҰ123283 men \add вүҲmade it\add* to RimmonВҰ123281 rock, andВҰ123275 they stayed there for four monthsВҰ123289.
\v 48 \add вүҲMeanwhile, the IsraelisВҰ123292\add* went back to the Benyamite \add region\add* and killed the people withВҰ123317 their swordsВҰ123301вҖ”entireВҰ123312 cities includingВҰ123298 cattle and everythingВҰ123308 elseвҖ”thenВҰ123291 the cities were set onВҰ123317 fire.
\c 21
\s1 Wives for the Benyamites
\rem /s1 The Benjaminites Saved from Extinction; Wives for the Tribe of Benjamin; Wives for the Benjamites; Israel Provides Wives for Benjamin
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* \add back\add* inВҰ123323 Mitspah, the IsraeliВҰ123320 menВҰ123320 had promisedВҰ123322 never to allow their daughtersВҰ123330 \add вүҲto marry\add* a Benyamite man.
\v 2 \add вүҲButВҰ123334\add* \add now\add* the IsraelisВҰ123336 wentВҰ123334 to Beyt-El and sat thereВҰ123340 before GodВҰ123345 untilВҰ123341 eveningВҰ123343вҖ”calling out and crying loudly,
\v 3 \add вүҲasking\add*, вҖңOh YahwehВҰ123354, GodВҰ123355 of Yisrael \add (IsraelВҰ123356)\add*, why has this happenedВҰ123357 to YisraelвҖ”for one tribeВҰ123363 \add вүҲto be missingВҰ123360\add* from Yisrael \add вүҲnow\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 The next dayВҰ123367, the peopleВҰ123369 got up earlyВҰ123368 and builtВҰ123370 an altarВҰ123373 thereВҰ123372, and they offered up burntВҰ123375 offerings and peaceВҰ123376 offerings.
\v 5 Then the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ123381 asked\add*, вҖңAmong all the IsraeliВҰ123381 tribesВҰ123390 serving Yahweh, \add вүҲwas there any group who didn't join the battle\add*?вҖқ (\add They asked that\add* because theyВҰ123379 had \add вүҲpreviously decided that anyoneВҰ123383 who didn't go to Mitspah to fight for Yahweh would\add* be put to deathВҰ123409.)
\v 6 \add вүҲNow the IsraelisВҰ123413 felt sorry for their Benyamite cousins\add*, saying, вҖңAn \add entire\add* tribeВҰ123421 has been \add вүҲhacked off\add* YisraelВҰ123413 today.
\v 7 \add вүҲHow can we find wives for any\add* \add Benyamite\add* men that are left because we've promisedВҰ123432 to YahwehВҰ123433 not to give our daughtersВҰ123438 to them \add вүҲto marry\add*?
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ123441\add* theyВҰ123441 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңIs there any \add вүҲfrom our tribesВҰ123444\add* who didn'tВҰ123447 \add вүҲshow up for\add* YahwehВҰ123452 at Mitspah?вҖқ ThenВҰ123441 listen, no one from Yabesh-Gilead had \add вүҲjoined their assemblyВҰ123466\add* \add there\add*.
\v 9 (\add вүҲWhenВҰ123468\add* the peopleВҰ123469 had \add вүҲchecked around\add* themselves, \add they'd realised that\add* no one from YabeshВҰ123477-Gilead was there.)
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ123479 the Israelis\add* sentВҰ123479 twelve thousandВҰ123486 \add вүҲwarriors\add* thereВҰ123481, commandingВҰ123490 them to use their swordsВҰ123502 to kill the inhabitantsВҰ123497 of YabeshВҰ123499-Gilead, includingВҰ123490 \add married\add* womenВҰ123503 andВҰ123479 \add вүҲchildren\add*вҖ”
\v 11 \add specifically\add* they had to killВҰ123520 every male, andВҰ123506 every womanВҰ123515 who's \add вүҲslept with\add* a male.
\v 12 \add That way\add* they discovered fourВҰ123527 hundredВҰ123528 youngВҰ123529 virginВҰ123530 women amongВҰ123523 the inhabitantsВҰ123523 of YabeshВҰ123526-Gilead, andВҰ123522 broughtВҰ123538 them \add back\add* to their campВҰ123542 at ShilohВҰ123543 (in the CanaanВҰ123546 \add regionВҰ123545\add*).
\p
\v 13 Then the entireВҰ123550 assembly sentВҰ123549 a message to the \add вүҲBenyamites\add* atВҰ123559 RimmonВҰ123560 rockВҰ123559, \add вүҲsaying that theyВҰ123553 were now ready for peaceВҰ123563\add*.
\v 14 SoВҰ123565 the \add вүҲBenyamites\add* returnedВҰ123565 andВҰ123565 were given the young women from YabeshВҰ123576-Gilead, \add вүҲbutВҰ123565\add* there wasn't enough of them.
\p
\v 15 The peopleВҰ123583 \add still\add* felt sorry for the \add вүҲBenyamites\add*, because YahwehВҰ123589 had \add вүҲcaused\add* a gap among Yisrael'sВҰ123592 tribesВҰ123591,
\v 16 \add вүҲso the leaders asked\add*, вҖңHow can weВҰ123599 provide wivesВҰ123601 for the remainingВҰ123600 \add @Benyamite men\add* since \add the other\add* Benyamite women \add вүҲwere wiped out\add*?вҖқ
\v 17 \add Because\add* theyВҰ123608 saidВҰ123608, вҖң\add вүҲThey mustВҰ123614 be able to procreate so that\add* an entire Israeli tribeВҰ123615 isn'tВҰ123612 blotted out.
\v 18 \add вүҲButВҰ123618 we can'tВҰ123619 be the ones to giveВҰ123621 our daughtersВҰ123625 to them to marry because we made an oath that anyoneВҰ123634 who did that would\add* be cursedВҰ123633.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 They saidВҰ123639, вҖңListen, there's a celebration for YahwehВҰ123643 from time to time atВҰ123644 ShilohВҰ123644, whichВҰ123648 is on the northВҰ123649 of Beyt-El, east of the road thatВҰ123648 goesВҰ123656 from Beyt-El uphill to ShechemВҰ123660, and on the southВҰ123661 of LebonahВҰ123662.вҖқ
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ123664\add* theyВҰ123664 \add вүҲtoldВҰ123664 the Benyamites\add*, вҖңGo andВҰ123673 hide inВҰ123674 those vineyardsВҰ123674
\v 21 and watchВҰ123676. \add вүҲWhenВҰ123695\add* the ShilohВҰ123683 girls come out to \add вүҲperform\add* inВҰ123685 the dancesВҰ123684, come out of the vineyardsВҰ123689 and you can each catch a wife for yourselves, thenВҰ123676 go \add back home\add* to BenyaminВҰ123698.
\v 22 \add вүҲWhenВҰ123700\add* their fathersВҰ123704 or brothersВҰ123706 complainВҰ123707 to us, we'll tell them, вҖң\add вүҲLet them have them since we didn'tВҰ123716 find you for them. And you all won'tВҰ123716 be guiltyВҰ123727 of giving them to the Benyamites\add* \add because theyВҰ123703 stole them\add*.
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲSo that's what the Benyamites\add* didвҖ”they grabbed enough dancing girls to be their wivesВҰ123736, then they returnedВҰ123744 to their \add вүҲallocated land\add* and rebuiltВҰ123748 their citiesВҰ123751 and livedВҰ123752 inВҰ123753 them.
\v 24 The \add other\add* \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ123759\add* wentВҰ123765 back to their tribesВҰ123763 andВҰ123755 their familiesВҰ123764 inВҰ123760 the areas that \add вүҲhad been allocated to them\add*.
\p
\v 25 In thoseВҰ123771 daysВҰ123770, thereВҰ123772 was no kingВҰ123773 inВҰ123774 YisraelВҰ123774вҖ”everyone would \add just\add* do \add вүҲwhat seemed rightВҰ123776 to them\add*.\x + \xo 21:25: \xt Jdg 17:6.\x*
